 duplicate notifications at irregular intervals.: [4:13]\n    * Video display issues are device-specific, particularly on Samsung S24/S25 models.: [5:50]\n    * @Rishabh Kumar suggested investigating potential internal testing app conflicts.:',1,306,'2026-03-11 18:46:48','2026-03-13 05:55:48'),(542,'tech-lead-hima-standup-fri','2026-03-09','Any bugs fixed or reported yesterday?','Fixed the video screen bug and reported to bala',1,307,'2026-03-11 18:46:49','2026-03-13 05:56:40'),(543,'tech-lead-hima-standup-fri','2026-03-09','Any open bugs that need attention?','* Technical Notification and Display Problems\n    * Users are receiving duplicate notifications at irregular intervals.: [4:13]\n    * Video display issues are device-specific, particularly on Samsung S24/S25 models.: [5:50]\n    * @Rishabh Kumar suggested investigating potential internal testing app conflicts.:',2,307,'2026-03-11 18:46:49','2026-03-13 05:56:52'),(544,'tech-lead-hima-standup-fri','2026-03-09','What is the current feature being worked on?','* Ludo Game Development Challenges\n    * Remote user connection for Ludo game is experiencing performance issues.',1,NULL,'2026-03-11 18:46:49','2026-03-13 05:57:55'),(545,'tech-lead-hima-standup-fri','2026-03-09','Is it on track for the expected timeline?','Yes, it is going on track',2,NULL,'2026-03-11 18:46:49','2026-03-13 05:58:18'),(550,'tech-lead-hima-standup-fri','2026-03-16','What are you working on today?','Summary\n\n* Data Storage and Visibility Problem\n    * @Yuvanesh reported fixing an issue where data was being stored in the database but not displaying correctly [0:38].\n    * The data was being stored as \"individual call random cultures\" but was not immediately visible [0:38].\n    * @Yuvanesh confirmed that after changes were made, the issue was resolved, with data now being stored properly',1,312,'2026-03-11 18:47:03','2026-03-20 19:48:56'),(551,'tech-lead-hima-standup-fri','2026-03-16','Any bugs fixed or reported yesterday?','@Yuvanesh reported fixing an issue where data was being stored in the database but not displaying correctly',1,313,'2026-03-11 18:47:03','2026-03-20 19:49:12'),(553,'tech-lead-hima-standup-fri','2026-03-16','What is the current feature being worked on?','A discussion arose about the payment screen showing empty without payment options, which @Rishabh Kumar explained is not a significant issue due to UPI app availability',1,314,'2026-03-11 18:47:03','2026-03-22 13:16:56'),(554,'tech-lead-hima-standup-fri','2026-03-16','Is it on track for the expected timeline?','yes it is going as per the expected timeline',2,314,'2026-03-11 18:47:03','2026-03-22 13:19:00'),(555,'tech-lead-hima-standup-fri','2026-03-16','Any release planned or pushed today?','No nothing like that',1,315,'2026-03-11 18:47:03','2026-03-22 13:20:04'),(556,'tech-lead-hima-standup-fri','2026-03-16','Any post-release issues from the last build?','to be updated in the next sprint ,@Raksha Agarwal will focus on retesting items in \"ready for QA\" and \"in progress\" status',2,315,'2026-03-11 18:47:03','2026-03-22 13:20:29'),(557,'tech-lead-hima-standup-fri','2026-03-16','Any blockers or issues..','No blockers as of now',1,316,'2026-03-11 18:47:03','2026-03-22 13:20:39'),(558,'tech-lead-hima-standup','2026-03-16','What tasks were completed yesterday?','1. Tested the HI Ma app for UI and functionality.\n2. Verified different modules like login, homepage, profile, and calling features.\n3. Identified several issues during testing.\n4. Logged multiple critical and high-priority bugs in the defect tracking system.',1,317,'2026-03-11 18:47:05','2026-03-16 05:32:23'),(559,'tech-lead-hima-standup','2026-03-16','What are you working on today?','1. Continue testing the HI Ma app. \n2. Verify the reported bugs after fixes (retesting) once the developer resolves them.\n3. Perform additional UI and functional testing.',1,318,'2026-03-11 18:47:05','2026-03-16 05:33:27'),(562,'tech-lead-hima-standup','2026-03-16','What is the current feature being worked on?','* Work Distribution\n    * @Raksha Agarwal initially suggested creating separate sprints for developers and QA for easier tracking, but @Yuvanesh cautioned against potential confusion. [10:44]\n    * Work schedule will be flexible, focusing on bugs first (Monday-Tuesday) and then new features, with adjustments based on Snega\'s work priority. [11:56]\n    * @Yuvanesh will consult with Megan and Bala to finalize the work plan. [12:39]',1,320,'2026-03-11 18:47:05','2026-03-16 14:42:04'),(563,'tech-lead-hima-standup','2026-03-16','Is it on track for the expected timeline?','yes it is going on track for the timeline',2,320,'2026-03-11 18:47:05','2026-03-16 14:43:46'),(564,'tech-lead-hima-standup','2026-03-16','Any release planned or pushed today?','No nothing is pushed today',1,321,'2026-03-11 18:47:05','2026-03-16 14:44:31'),(565,'tech-lead-hima-standup','2026-03-16','Any post-release issues from the last build?','As of now no issues are reported',2,321,'2026-03-11 18:47:05','2026-03-16 14:44:52'),(568,'tech-lead-hima-standup','2026-03-09','What are you working on today?','* Sprint Planning\n    * @Yuvanesh outlined two sprints: one from 16-22 and another from 23-29.\n    * Bugs have been separated into groups, with some assigned to the current week\'s sprint and others to next week\'s sprint. \n    * New bugs will be added to next week\'s sprint, and bugs being solved this week will be added to the current sprint.',1,324,'2026-03-11 18:49:53','2026-03-16 11:25:09'),(569,'tech-lead-hima-standup','2026-03-09','Any bugs fixed or reported yesterday?','All previous UI sprint bugs completed',1,325,'2026-03-11 18:49:53','2026-03-16 11:25:31'),(570,'tech-lead-hima-standup','2026-03-09','Any open bugs that need attention?','no open bugs as of now',2,325,'2026-03-11 18:49:53','2026-03-16 11:25:44'),(571,'tech-lead-hima-standup','2026-03-09','What is the current feature being worked on?','Currently working on two new sprints',1,326,'2026-03-11 18:49