-03-24 18:40:12','2026-03-25 09:20:21'),(1627,'content_lead-creative-planning-execution-meet-wed','2026-03-23','What content was created/published yesterday?','Summary\n\n* Video Project Concept\n    * @Krishnan Krishnan outlined a romantic video scenario involving a nighttime 1-to-1 video call between a guy and a girl [3:06].\n    * The concept is based on a previous reference video, featuring casual conversation and potentially romantic dialogue [3:33].\n    * The scene should depict the couple lying down and talking, with a focus on creating an attractive and romantic atmosphere [3:57].\n* Image Generation Process\n    * @Krishnan Krishnan recommended using AI to analyze a reference image and generate a detailed prompt for new image creation [5:23].\n    * Team will use cloud premium and a shared creative ID for image generation [4:48].\n    * The goal is to create an attractive nighttime scene with multiple potential poses [5:53].\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @tiyasa and @Maanasi to generate a script for the romantic video scenario [4:06].\n* Team to create initial image using reference and AI-generated prompt [5:23].\n* @Krishnan Krishnan will share the fixed creative ID for cloud platform access [5:23].\n* Get project approval before proceeding with video generation [4:06].\n* Monitor Higgs field credits and request top-up if needed [4:23].',1,1112,'2026-03-25 03:59:16','2026-03-25 10:33:16'),(1628,'content_lead-creative-planning-execution-meet-wed','2026-03-23','What content is planned for today?',':star: Summary\n\n* Content Creation Workflow\n    * @Krishnan Krishnan outlined a structured approach for content creation across different days: Monday for audio calls, Tuesday for video calls, Wednesday for UGC videos, and Thursday-Friday reserved for creative exploration [5:32].\n    * The team will use a new Google sheet to track daily content, allowing paste of scripts and performance monitoring [6:32].\n* Video Generation Techniques\n    * @Krishnan Krishnan recommended using multiple short angles for more engaging video content, suggesting scenes that show progression like a character preparing or changing [8:28].\n    * Guidance provided to limit video generation to 6 videos per project to minimize potential mistakes [9:01].\n    * @Disha P noted Claude is better at understanding content generation compared to ChatGPT [4:14].\n* Tools and Resources\n    * @Krishnan Krishnan recommended using Claude for content generation, image creation, and creative ideation [4:24].\n    * The team discussed using Cloud for generating more realistic images and videos [3:54].\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @Maanasi to search and propose new content ideas by next meeting [7:36].\n* @tiyasa to track and gently remind Anna about pending video scripts, aiming to collect all videos by Friday or Saturday [2:34].\n* Team to start using Claude for content and image generation [4:24].\n* @Krishnan Krishnan will create a Google sheet for tracking daily content creation [6:32].\n* Await meta dashboard from Ruth, expected by next week [9:53].',1,1113,'2026-03-25 03:59:16','2026-03-25 10:30:41'),(1629,'content_lead-creative-planning-execution-meet-wed','2026-03-23','Any scripts or assets pending review?','',1,1114,'2026-03-25 03:59:16','2026-03-25 03:59:16'),(1630,'content_lead-creative-planning-execution-meet-wed','2026-03-23','Any blockers or dependencies?','',1,1115,'2026-03-25 03:59:17','2026-03-25 03:59:17'),(1631,'tech-lead-onlycare-standup-wed','2026-03-23','What tasks were completed yesterday?','Testing for the registration event was completed by Mari Muthu, and the system was verified as working by Yuvanesh',1,1121,'2026-03-25 04:51:19','2026-03-30 03:47:02'),(1632,'tech-lead-onlycare-standup-wed','2026-03-23','What are you working on today?','Mari Muthu is working on completing full payout integration, and Yuvanesh is planning to create a Slack group for team communication',1,1122,'2026-03-25 04:51:19','2026-03-30 03