r acquisition. [14:59]\n    * The leadership requires clear justification and performance metrics for marketing expenditures. [13:49]\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @Nandha to analyze and confirm the number of conversation scripts needed for each language. [45:24]\n* @Krishnan Krishnan to coordinate with team members to ensure the new 25-videos-per-month content creation plan is implemented starting Monday. [43:50]\n* @anindita to research potential Ugadi festival-specific content that could increase app registrations. [23:15]\n* Team to prepare 20 new video creatives each for Marathi, Bengali, and Kannada languages by late March. [25:13]\n* @anindita to explore potential regional influencer collaborations, particularly in the Marathi market. [27:26]',3,'2026-03-13 11:24:43','2026-03-13 11:24:43'),(35,'ceo-ai-standup-fri','2026-03-09',':headphones: Huddle notes: 13/03/2026 with @J P and @Sneha PratapSlack AI took notes for this huddle from 15:43:03 - 16:24:22 GMT+5:30. A detailed technical discussion between two developers about the design and implementation of a mobile application, focusing on user interface, character creation, and core functionality. View huddle in channel\n\n:handshake: Attendees\n\n@J P and @Sneha Pratap\n\n:star: Summary\n\n* App Screen and Character Design\n    * @J P discussed the character selection screen, which involves choosing gender and creating a profile [19:24].\n    * The app includes a character creation process with multiple steps, including entering name and selecting profile characteristics [18:58].\n    * There are plans to offer 10 different character behavior options for users to choose from [19:24].\n* Technical Implementation\n    * @J P is working on connecting API for different app screens and exploring various functionalities [37:47].\n    * The development process involves creating login, registration, and profile setup elements [38:30].\n    * Integration with 3D elements and user authentication are part of the development scope [39:04].\n* Project Timeline\n    * @Sneha Pratap mentioned a project timeline spanning 16-20th March, with approximately 5 days of work [5:58].\n    * The team plans to complete around 55 tasks, with 44 potentially completed in a day [6:08].\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @J P to complete API integration for different app screens [37:47].\n* @J P to finalize character creation process, including 10 behavior options [19:24].\n* @Sneha Pratap to review and validate the 55-task project plan for the 16-20th March period [6:08].\n* Complete the login, registration, and profile setup implementation [38:30].',1,'2026-03-13 11:38:16','2026-03-13 11:40:09'),(36,'ceo-ai-standup-thu','2026-03-09',':headphones: Huddle notes: 12/03/2026 with @J P and @Sneha PratapSlack AI took notes for this huddle from 11:39:06 - 12:45:27 GMT+5:30. The meeting focused on developing an innovative AI character interaction platform, discussing technical implementation, voice cloning, and long-term strategic vision for creating more natural AI personas. View huddle in channel\n\n:handshake: Attendees\n\n@J P, @Sneha Pratap, @Fida Taneem and @Yuvanesh\n\n:star: Summary\n\n* AI Persona Development Architecture\n    * @Sneha Pratap explained a multi-layered approach to AI persona creation, including layers for chat persistence, personality generation, and context understanding: [22:24].\n    * The architecture aims to create more nuanced AI interactions that go beyond simple data retrieval, focusing on contextual understanding and adaptive responses.\n    * Key challenges include reducing the perception of AI artificiality and creating more natural, context-aware communication.\n* Voice Cloning Technology\n    * @Fida Taneem described the voice cloning process, which requires 20-30 minutes of voice recording to generate a voice ID and API: [19:58].\n    * The technology involves using an LLM to understand messages, generate text responses, and then convert those responses into a cloned voice.\n    * Contextual data and personality traits are crucial for creating a more authentic voice clone.\n* Platform Commercialization Strategy\n    * @J P proposed a long-term vision of creating a platform with 25 distinct character types, potentially expanding to 200 characters: [35:29].\n    * The strategy involves collecting diverse interaction data to improve AI personas and create more nuanced communication styles.\n    * Future possibilities include features like AI-powered dating interactions and regional character variations.\n* Technical Implementation and Rules\n    * @J P discussed implementing rules to prevent data deletion and maintain consistent project standards: [50:51].\n    * The team aims to create a flexible system that can guide AI behavior while preventing unintended actions.\n    * Rules can help manage database access, define project color schemes, and provide context for different interactions.\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @Sneha Pratap to continue developing the multi-layered AI persona architecture with a focus on reducing artificial communication: [42:02].\n* @Fida Taneem to explore and potentially subscribe to a voice cloning platform: [46:14].\n* @J P to further develop the rules and constraints for AI interaction platform: [51:21].\n* Create a sprint for Unman and video app development, focusing on implementing the new AI persona architecture: [9:38].',1,'2026-03-13 11:42:10','2026-03-13 11:42:10'),(37,'tech-lead-sudar-thedal-standup-fri','2026-03-09','Summary\n\n* Dashboard Data Inconsistency\n    * @Tamil reported that the dashboard is showing different data values on consecutive days, specifically noting discrepancies between payment gateway records\n    * The inconsistency appears to be a systemic issue where data representation changes unexpectedly between days.\n* Technical Process Improvement\n    * @Yuvanesh provided guidance to @Sivaperumal on creating comprehensive rule sets and conditions for code management, emphasizing the importance of controlled, intentional changes\n* Recommended implementing conditional logic that prompts for confirmation before making significant modifications, such as changing digit formats or accessing specific data tables.\n    * Discussed GPT usage efficiency, noting that @Sivaperumal has used 38.5% of the subscription in approximately 10 days\n* Current Development Status\n    * @Sivaperumal is currently working on a Spring Boot project with multiple unresolved bugs.\n    * The team is focusing on systematic debugging and documentation of development processes.',34,'2026-03-16 03:00:25','2026-03-16 03:02:21'),(38,'ceo-ai-standup','2026-03-16','Slack AI took notes for this huddle from 10:32:15 - 10:42:39 GMT+5:30. The meeting covered multiple ongoing technology projects, focusing on AI verification, voice cloning, and a video creation platform, with discussions about technical challenges and next steps. View huddle in channel\n\n:handshake: Attendees\n\n@Fida Taneem, @J P and @Sneha Pratap\n\n:star: Summary\n\n* KYC AI Verification Project\n    * @Fida Taneem demonstrated a significant performance improvement in PAN verification, reducing processing time from 60 hours to 4-5 hours with minimal human intervention [4:04].\n    * The finance team has positively received the solution, testing a file of 6,400 PAN verifications that take 2-3 seconds per verification [4:04].\n* Voice Cloning Project\n    * @J P proposed an interactive, real-time voice cloning system where users can chat with a cloned voice, responding in the original speaker\'s voice [5:57].\n    * @Fida Taneem indicated that the chat infrastructure is already built, and the next step is integrating voice capabilities [6:26].\n* Video Creation Platform\n    * @Sneha Pratap reported significant technical issues with the current platform, including login errors that prompt users to sign out and log in again [7:41].\n    * The current developer has expressed inability to resolve the issues, leading to discussions about reassigning or resolving the problems [7:13].\n* Holiday Planning\n    * @Fida Taneem noted that the exact holiday date is uncertain and depends on the moon sighting by the Delhi Islamic community [11:37].\n    * The team is awaiting official confirmation before finalizing holiday plans [10:58].\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @Fida Taneem to complete the video creation platform debugging before starting the voice cloning project [8:47].\n* @Sneha Pratap will connect with @Fida Taneem after the meeting to provide details about platform bugs [8:57].\n* @Fida Taneem to focus on voice cloning project after resolving the video platform issues [9:25].\n* Team to await official moon sighting confirmation for holiday scheduling [11:37].',1,'2026-03-16 05:16:27','2026-03-16 05:16:27'),(39,'full-stack-dev-astro-standup','2026-03-16','Summary\n\n* Website and Chat Development Status\n    * @Rishabh Kumar confirmed that the website is prepared to go live: [3:03].\n    * @Barkha Agarwal has been working on saving chat history and images for multiple astrologers: [1:38].\n    * Current technical work appears to be functioning properly according to both participants: [2:09].\n* Chat Humanization Request\n    * @Rishabh Kumar requested that chat responses be made more human-like, suggesting backend prompts to make astrologer messages feel more authentic and natural: [3:14].\n    * @Barkha Agarwal acknowledged understanding the request and agreed to work on this aspect: [3:39].',39,'2026-03-16 05:46:45','2026-03-16 08:42:33'),(40,'ops-standup-daily','2026-03-16','* Tessa Portal Dashboard Introduction\n    * @Sneha Sunoj explained the mandatory sign-in process for the new Tessa portal dashboard, emphasizing that attendance will only be marked when team members complete the sign-in procedure [9:13].\n    * The dashboard includes sections for daily reports, meetings, calendar, and team KPIs that must be consistently updated [4:04].\n    * Daily reports must be filled out retrospectively (e.g., Monday\'s report on Tuesday) with specific guidelines for tracking tickets resolved and work completed [4:21].\n\n\n* Performance Metrics Review\n    * Team members reported individual performance metrics, including onboarding numbers and ticket resolutions for Friday and Thursday [6:44].\n    * @Deeksha reported 23 onboardings and 28 tickets on Friday [7:15], @Reshma Reshma reported 21 onboardings and 22 tickets [7:47], and @Gousia reported 43 onboardings and 74 tickets [8:23].\n    * @Sneha Sunoj emphasized the importance of maintaining a proper review structure and tracking performance consistently [8:44].\n* Technical Issues and Complaints\n    * @Sneha Sunoj discussed ongoing technical problems including recharge page issues, call connection problems, and user deduction concerns [10:07].\n    * The team was instructed to provide detailed complaint information, specifying the number of users experiencing each issue to help prioritize problem resolution [10:39].\n    * Some issues, like creator call deduction policies, cannot be modified without impacting company revenue [12:32].\n\nFeatures to be Added:\n\nAdd a reason box for the block option.\n2. In the ticket section, include an option to attach photos or videos.\n3. In the ticket filter, ensure that selected filters remain applied even after resolving tickets.\n4. Add Review Bonus and Target Bonus entries in the transaction section to track bonus-related transactions.',5,'2026-03-16 06:25:21','2026-03-16 09:48:13'),(41,'marketing-standup-daily','2026-03-16','Summary\n\n* Language-wise Performance Analysis\n    * @Nandha reviewed registration numbers across different languages, including Malayalam (361 registrations), Telugu (223), Kannada (308), and Tamil (279).[17:15]- [18:00]\n    * The team observed variations in Return on Ad Spend (ROAs) across languages, with Tamil at 2.86, Telugu at 2.6, and Kannada at 1.91.[21:29]- [21:52]\n* Budget and Campaign Strategy\n    * @Nandha recommended increasing the budget by ₹5,000 for certain campaigns and suggested creating new campaigns with language-specific targeting.[9:31]- [15:58]\n    * The team discussed the potential of Google Ads, noting that it might have less creative saturation compared to other platforms.[7:05]- [7:15]\n* Creative Performance\n    * @Anirudh planned to focus on creative development, with a full focus on new creatives planned for the next Monday.[14:15]- [14:23]\n    * The team acknowledged the importance of testing different creative approaches to improve campaign performance.[14:23]- [14:48]\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @Anirudh to develop new creatives and prepare for testing different creative approaches by next Monday.[14:15]- [14:23]\n* @Nandha to increase campaign budgets by ₹5,000 and create new language-specific campaigns.[9:31]- [15:58]\n* Review and optimize campaigns focusing on languages with lower ROAs, particularly Kannada.[21:52]',3,'2026-03-16 06:32:33','2026-03-16 06:32:33'),(42,'product_manager-daily-standup-dhanush','2026-03-16','1. trail taken follow ups\n2. 7th day only seen \n3. Meeting will conduct in marketing manger\n4. if any thing app side issue escalation',2,'2026-03-16 07:07:49','2026-03-16 07:10:15'),(43,'cmo-anindita-daily-standup','2026-03-16','Summary\n\n* User Data and Conversion Metrics\n    * @Nandha shared screen demonstrating registration and paid user account data: [6:30].\n    * The team needs to calculate conversion rates by comparing total registrations to total paid users: [6:41].\n    * Average paying amount will be calculated by dividing total revenue by total number of paid users: [6:51].\n* Bengali Campaign Performance\n    * Recent Bengali campaign registration numbers have been inconsistent, with 142 registrations on one notable day: [12:34].\n    * @Nandha acknowledged the campaign needs optimization and plans to increase campaign spending by ₹5000: [13:13].\n    * Current day\'s data shows 47 registrations and approximately 2000 in total recharge: [13:20].\n* New Intern Hiring\n    * A new performance marketing intern has been hired with approximately 6 months of previous experience: [8:49].\n    * The intern is currently in a probation period and will transition to a full-time role after this period: [9:29].\n    * It is a paid internship starting immediately: [9:52].\n* Daily Reporting Process\n    * A new daily data update system has been implemented requiring immediate and consistent data entry: [11:56].\n    * Once a day passes, data for that day cannot be edited: [12:10].\n    * Key metrics to track daily include CPA (Cost Per Acquisition) and other performance indicators: [14:29].\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @anindita will update last week\'s data retrospectively and start daily data entry from today: [11:38].\n* @Nandha will increase Bengali campaign spending by ₹5000 to optimize performance: [13:13].\n* @anindita will follow up with @Nandha daily to ensure comprehensive metric tracking: [14:13].\n* Track daily registration numbers, total recharge, and CPA for the Bengali campaign: [13:47].',3,'2026-03-16 07:33:04','2026-03-16 07:33:04'),(44,'cmo-creative-team-daily-standup','2026-03-16','Summary\n\n* Video Production Strategy\n    * @Nandha emphasized producing 5 videos daily and updating the project portal consistently. [7:28]\n    * @Krishnan Krishnan suggested focusing on 1-to-1 conversation style videos and pre-editing content across multiple languages including Tamil, Hindi, Bengali, and Telugu. [8:18]\n* Content Creation Workflow\n    * @Nandha highlighted the importance of daily video uploads and portal updates to track progress. [2:08]\n    * The team discussed creating content for various language markets to expand reach. [7:02]\n* Social Media and Hiring\n    * @Nandha mentioned potential hiring for a social media manager and content quality testing role. [10:25]\n    * @Sooraj discussed creating content across different languages and translating materials. [9:36]\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @Nandha to ensure daily production of 5 videos and consistent portal updates. [7:28]\n* @Krishnan Krishnan to coordinate video script preparation and pre-editing for multiple language markets. [8:18]\n* @Sooraj to continue creating daily posters and translating content across languages. [10:00]\n* Team to explore hiring a social media manager and content quality tester. [10:25]',3,'2026-03-16 07:33:34','2026-03-16 07:33:34'),(45,'ops-coo-weekly','2026-03-16','1. creators\' earnings amount issues\n2. user busy\n3. In user side improperly coins dectued\n\n\nif there any issue  means need count must\nlast week KPI\'s sneha will update after that i will set target',2,'2026-03-16 07:43:59','2026-03-16 07:52:25'),(46,'product_manager-daily-standup-tamil','2026-03-16','1. Need to focus on trails & premium don\'t much more time spend in tech part\nanalysis the content for IN app side',2,'2026-03-16 07:51:34','2026-03-16 07:51:34'),(48,'cfo-stand-up-meeting','2026-03-16','Slack AI took notes for this huddle from 14:54:37 - 15:20:49 GMT+5:30. A meeting between @Ayush Agarwal and @Shoyab focusing on financial documentation, asset tracking, and GST-related tasks, with an emphasis on improving organizational processes. View huddle in channel\n\n:handshake: Attendees\n\n@Shoyab and @Ayush Agarwal\n\n:star: Summary\n\n* Asset Register and Documentation\n    * @Ayush Agarwal confirmed completion of the asset register work process: [2:12].\n    * Discussed tracking of laptop purchases, including verifying whether initial laptops were provided by JP or purchased separately: [10:41].\n    * Explored strategies for better invoice and asset documentation, including potential system improvements for tracking purchases: [14:30].\n* GST and Financial Reporting\n    * @Shoyab is currently working on GST 3B filing: [4:41].\n    * Discussed details of GST calculations, including potential amounts around 92,000 and 22 lakhs: [23:03].\n    * Reviewed GST collection and reporting requirements: [23:45].\n* Invoice and Expense Management\n    * Discussed challenges in tracking and organizing invoices, particularly for expenses: [17:42].\n    * Proposed solutions include renaming invoices with vendor name, invoice number, and date: [18:04].\n    * Considered using Google Sheets and system downloads to improve tracking: [14:30].\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @Shoyab to complete GST 3B filing and verify calculations: [25:17].\n* @Ayush Agarwal and @Shoyab to develop a consistent invoice naming and tracking system: [19:53].\n* Review and confirm the origin of laptop purchases (JP-provided vs. company-purchased): [10:41].\n* Explore using Google Drive or alternative systems for better document management: [14:48].',32,'2026-03-16 09:53:57','2026-03-23 06:24:40'),(49,'content_lead-creative-planning-execution-meet','2026-03-16','Summary\n\n* Video Production Workflow\n    * @Krishnan Krishnan outlined the project goal of producing approximately 100 videos in 15 days, with an initial target of one video per day. [3:25]\n    * The team will gradually scale up production from 1 to potentially 5-11 videos daily. [7:03]\n    * The workflow involves script writing, audio generation using 11 Labs, and video creation through Higgs field. [4:41]\n* Technical Requirements\n    * Scripts should be concise, approximately 30-40 seconds in length. [8:40]\n    * Audio will be generated using 11 Labs, with team members translating scripts into local languages like Bengali. [3:20]\n    * Video generation will use Higgs field with pre-existing prompts and templates. [6:08]\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @Maanasi will rewrite and refine the sunset-themed script, ensuring it meets the 30-40 second requirement. [8:37]\n* @tiyasa will complete the Bengali translation of the script and generate corresponding audio and video. [3:16]\n* All team members should complete their initial script and audio generation by end of day. [6:49]\n* @Krishnan Krishnan will review and approve scripts before final video production. [4:14]',20,'2026-03-16 10:11:50','2026-03-16 10:11:50'),(50,'tech-lead-hima-standup','2026-03-09','Summary\n\n* Sprint Planning\n    * @Yuvanesh outlined two sprints: one from 16-22 and another from 23-29. \n    * Bugs have been separated into groups, with some assigned to the current week\'s sprint and others to next week\'s sprint. \n    * New bugs will be added to next week\'s sprint, and bugs being solved this week will be added to the current sprint. \n* Work Distribution\n    * @Raksha Agarwal initially suggested creating separate sprints for developers and QA for easier tracking, but @Yuvanesh cautioned against potential confusion. \n    * Work schedule will be flexible, focusing on bugs first (Monday-Tuesday) and then new features, with adjustments based on Snega\'s work priority. \n    * @Yuvanesh will consult with Megan and Bala to finalize the work plan. \n\nAction items\n\n* @Yuvanesh to discuss work priorities with Megan and Bala to confirm the final work distribution. \n* @Rishabh Kumar to focus on bugs first, then transition to new features based on priority. \n* Team to track and assign bugs across the current and next sprint as discussed.',34,'2026-03-16 12:33:32','2026-03-16 12:33:32'),(51,'tech-lead-onlycare-standup','2026-03-09','Summary\n\n* App Call Screen Modifications\n    * @Mari Muthu discussed changes recommended by @Bala to standardize the UI for personal and random call screens. \n    * The suggestion was to use a consistent connecting screen design across different call types. \n* Dashboard Data Review\n    * @Mari Muthu identified discrepancies in dashboard data, noting that some sections are showing incorrect or delayed information. \n    * The team plans to review and correct dashboard metrics, potentially involving a separate meeting to address specific issues. \n* Development Timeline\n    * @Yuvanesh outlined a detailed plan for the upcoming week, including implementing changes, preparing the APK, and integrating the SDK. [15:28]\n    * The team aims to complete the app launch preparation by the end of the current week. [9:24]\n\n\n* @Mari Muthu to implement UI changes for call screens within 5 hours. \n* @Mari Muthu to prepare and send a document detailing the changes discussed with @Bala. \n* @Mari Muthu to compare current dashboard with Haima\'s dashboard and document necessary changes. \n* Team to finalize APK and prepare for SDK integration by Wednesday. \n* Conduct a follow-up meeting specifically to discuss dashboard improvements.',34,'2026-03-16 14:22:48','2026-03-16 14:22:48'),(52,'tech-lead-sudar-thedal-standup','2026-03-09','YESTERDAY\'S WORK - Final apk work submited to the team \n\nToday work -Rules for cursor and dashboard changes documentation \n\nPRODUCT UPDATES - Issue in dashboard data accuracy which is getting fixed by razorpay api \n\nFeature progress update - Apk under review with bala he will decide on the new feautres \n\nAction Items - \n\nPerumal to send documentation of rules to be implemented  for dashboard accuracy\n\nBala to send Final APK documentation',34,'2026-03-16 14:34:05','2026-03-16 14:34:05'),(53,'tech-lead-hima-standup','2026-03-16','Summary\n\n* Sprint Planning\n    * @Yuvanesh outlined two sprints: one from 16-22 and another from 23-29. [9:32]\n    * Bugs have been separated into groups, with some assigned to the current week\'s sprint and others to next week\'s sprint. [9:52]\n    * New bugs will be added to next week\'s sprint, and bugs being solved this week will be added to the current sprint. [10:20]\n* Work Distribution\n    * @Raksha Agarwal initially suggested creating separate sprints for developers and QA for easier tracking, but @Yuvanesh cautioned against potential confusion. [10:44]\n    * Work schedule will be flexible, focusing on bugs first (Monday-Tuesday) and then new features, with adjus