rformance optimization [7:32].',2,'2026-03-17 06:40:52','2026-03-17 07:07:25'),(60,'cmo-creative-team-daily-standup-tue','2026-03-16','Attendees\n\n@Nandha, @Krishnan Krishnan, @anas and @Sooraj\n\n:star: Summary\n\n* Video Content Strategy\n    * @Nandha discussed creating videos targeting different audience segments, with specific focus on female and male influencers. [3:34]\n    * The team explored UGC (User Generated Content) strategies, considering both male and female content creators. [3:25]\n    * Discussion included potential content in multiple languages, including Bengali and Tamil. [4:53]\n* Marketing Approach\n    * @Nandha indicated interest in performance tracking and daily updates for marketing initiatives. [1:19]\n    * The team considered targeting specific audience demographics through video content. [3:54]\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @Nandha to update and track performance on weekend checkpoints. [1:35]\n* @Sooraj to review and potentially modify existing posters and marketing materials. [5:13]\n* Team to continue exploring UGC content creation strategies across different language markets. [4:38]',3,'2026-03-17 07:26:50','2026-03-17 07:26:50'),(61,'cmo-anindita-daily-standup-tue','2026-03-16','Attendees\n\n@anindita and @Nandha\n\n:star: Summary\n\n* Campaign Performance Analysis\n    * @anindita observed that the current campaign is not showing significant improvements, with user reach remaining consistent with pre-campaign levels.[3:13]\n    * @Nandha confirmed that daily revenues have decreased while customer acquisition costs have increased.[3:58]\n* Campaign Name and Targeting Strategy\n    * @anindita suggested changing the campaign name to better reflect its purpose and capture the campaign\'s core objective.[6:44]\n    * @anindita proposed modifying audience targeting by focusing on profession, age, and location to improve campaign effectiveness.[7:04]\n    * The team recognized the importance of providing Meta with detailed audience characteristics to improve ad targeting precision.[9:24]\n* Language and Branding Considerations\n* Creative Content Development\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @anindita to redesign campaign name and targeting strategy for the Bengali market.[7:34]\n* @Nandha to work on generating more Bengali-specific creative videos to increase creator registrations.[12:45]\n* Upload existing user data to Meta to help refine audience targeting algorithms.[9:21]\n* Conduct a test run of the new targeting approach for 2-3 days to assess performance improvements.[7:34]',3,'2026-03-17 07:27:11','2026-03-17 07:27:11'),(62,'full-stack-dev-astro-standup-tue','2026-03-16','Summary\n\n* Repository Code Push Process\n    * @Rishabh Kumar guided @Barkha Agarwal through the process of pushing code to a specific repository [1:47].\n    * @Rishabh Kumar instructed @Barkha Agarwal to copy repository token and ensure correct repository details [2:57].\n    * Authentication challenges emerged during the code push attempt [6:15].\n* Technical Configuration Review\n    * @Rishabh Kumar examined the current configuration, specifically checking the open router key in the environment [0:59].\n    * They discussed the current key configuration and potential discrepancies [1:40].\n* Chat Interface Improvements\n    * @Rishabh Kumar highlighted that the current user chat interface lacks a human touch and contains excessive stars, making it feel unnatural: [6:26].\n    * The goal is to make the text communication feel more humanized and less mechanical.\n* Language Consistency\n    * @Rishabh Kumar noted an issue where the language of responses does not match the user\'s input language, specifically when a user texts in English but receives a response in Hindi: [6:26].\n    * Recommendation is to maintain language consistency based on the user\'s original communication language.\n* Development Next Steps\n    * @Rishabh Kumar mentioned that Yuvnesh will website live then he  test functiona