ent details and filing requirements carefully[30:43].\n* Invoice Collection Process\n    * @Shoyab proposed a centralized platform for team members to upload invoices, emphasizing consistency and ease of tracking[21:37].\n    * The suggestion includes automatic renaming of files and creating reminders for upload[21:55].\n    * @Ayush Agarwal supported the idea of a systematic approach to invoice management[22:17].\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @Shoyab to finalize and verify PF calculations for submission[34:58].\n* Prepare and submit GST payment for the current period[33:53].\n* Develop a centralized invoice upload platform with weekly submission requirements[20:59].\n* @Shoyab to potentially change system software, uninstalling VPS and installing Excel[38:28].\n* Review and confirm the final calculations for both PF and GST before submission[25:41].',32,'2026-03-18 10:25:27','2026-03-18 10:25:27'),(75,'ceo-ai-standup-wed','2026-03-16',':headphones: Huddle notes: 18/03/2026 with @J P and @Sneha PratapSlack AI took notes for this huddle from 11:36:11 - 11:56:22 GMT+5:30. Meeting discussed ongoing platform development, UI design for a chat application, and video workflow management, with @J P providing guidance and direction to the team. View huddle in channel\n\n:handshake: Attendees\n\n@Sneha Pratap, @J P and @Fida Taneem\n\n:star: Summary\n\n* Platform Development Status\n    * @J P emphasized the need for a clear, structured sprint plan with specific completion dates for the current platform development. [2:20]\n    * @Sneha Pratap indicated a meeting with Nanda at 12 o\'clock to discuss additional features. [2:41]\n    * @J P instructed the team to list out requirements, create a sprint plan, and provide detailed time estimates before proceeding. [4:18]\n* Chat Application UI/UX Design\n    * @J P requested a WhatsApp-like design with consistent color themes and login/OTP process. [9:21]\n    * @Sneha Pratap demonstrated a profile section with character selection and customization features. [8:38]\n    * The design includes options for user profile, character creation, and messaging interfaces. [9:41]\n* Video Workflow Dashboard\n    * @Sneha Pratap explained the video status tracking process, clarifying that only the creator approves videos, not the manager. [13:50]\n    * The dashboard categorizes videos into different states: assigned, overdue, rejected, and completed. [12:17]\n    * Krishna acts as a middleman in the approval process, receiving only approved videos. [14:01]\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @Fida Taneem to get requirements from Nanda and prepare a detailed sprint plan. [10:40]\n* @Sneha Pratap to complete the chat application UI, focusing on WhatsApp-like design and profile features. [6:12]\n* @Fida Taneem to create a Google Sheets document outlining feature development time estimates. [16:22]\n* Team to finalize platform development timeline and feature specifications. [3:27]\n\nThis tool uses AI to generate notes, so some information may be inaccurate. They\'re based on the huddle transcript and thread a',1,'2026-03-18 12:06:49','2026-03-18 12:06:49'),(76,'ops-standup-daily-fri','2026-03-16','* Payment and Credit Discrepancies\n    * @Sneha Sunoj identified a billing issue where an audio call was incorrectly charged, noting that a 52-minute, 8-second call should be billed at ₹53, not the current higher amount.[1:26]\n    * A ₹7788 credit for @Gousia was marked as paid but not actually credited to their account.[2:01]\n* Technical Platform Issues\n    * Multiple team members reported app loading problems, with creators unable to open the app and it only showing a loading screen.[7:57]\n    * Notifications are currently only generating in English, not in regional languages as required.[12:45]\n    * AI target achievement data was reported as incorrect.[7:16]\n* Team Performance Metrics\n    * @Ranjini reported 15 tickets and 20 onboardings on Wednesday.[5:03]\n    * @Deeksha completed 16