ative strategies.[16:27]\n    * The team discussed the importance of monitoring campaign performance and adjusting budgets accordingly across different languages and regions.[15:36]\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @Nandha to create a new retargeting campaign focusing on app installers who haven\'t made a purchase.[15:19]\n* @Anirudh to review and potentially reduce spending in Karnataka, targeting only 77,000 for 3 days.[18:49]\n* Review and optimize audience targeting, particularly for language-specific campaigns.[15:47]\n* Monitor campaign performance and adjust creative strategies based on winning ads.[16:27]',3,'2026-03-20 08:02:08','2026-03-20 08:02:08'),(83,'cmo-creative-team-daily-standup-fri','2026-03-16','Summary\n\n* Content Creation Discussion\n    * @Krishnan Krishnan appears to be seeking a different approach to creating a conversational script, potentially for a video project [0:38].\n    * The team discussed creating content in Bengali language, suggesting a targeted regional marketing effort [4:10].\n* Project Workflow\n    * @Sooraj mentioned a timeline of 3-5 hours for a specific task, indicating a structured project approach [5:14].\n    * There are indications of pending tasks and updates to be shared later in the afternoon [5:50].\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @Nandha to develop a content strategy for a project, potentially involving a video script in Bengali [4:26].\n* @Sooraj will share updates in the afternoon regarding pending items [5:50].\n* Team to finalize details of content creation and posting strategy [5:24].',3,'2026-03-20 09:01:38','2026-03-20 09:01:38'),(84,'cfo-stand-up-meeting-fri','2026-03-16','Slack AI took notes for this huddle from 13:20:22 - 15:20:30 GMT+5:30. A comprehensive meeting between @Ayush Agarwal and @Shoyab covering financial processes, including GST payment, PF calculations, and PAN card verification using various software tools. View huddle in channel\n\n:handshake: Attendees\n\n@Ayush Agarwal and @Shoyab\n\n:star: Summary\n\n* GST Payment Process\n    * @Ayush Agarwal and @Shoyab collaborated to complete a 52 lakh GST payment through Yes Bank corporate account: [21:03].\n    * They discussed potential bank transfer limitations and considered splitting the payment across multiple accounts: [9:02].\n    * The payment was successfully processed, with careful attention to portal timing and transaction details: [24:00].\n* PAN Card Verification Project\n    * @Shoyab consolidated PAN card details from multiple sources, starting with 11,818 entries: [55:20].\n    * Using Excel and Windman software, they reduced the list to 6,000 validated entries: [1:00:40].\n    * Identified 447 PAN cards requiring further investigation or verification: [1:09:17].\n* Financial Compliance and Reporting\n    * Discussed PF payments for December and January, noting some calculation complexities: [1:57:13].\n    * Planned to follow up on TDS streamlining and prepare for upcoming quarterly reporting: [1:56:52].\n    * Noted the upcoming April 7th deadline for certain payments and potential penalties: [1:57:13].\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @Shoyab to investigate the 447 PAN cards with potential verification issues: [1:09:17].\n* @Shoyab to explore Tally software licensing options and potential upgrades: [1:58:31].\n* @Shoyab to send PF payment details for January and February to @Ayush Agarwal: [1:59:44].\n* Prepare for TDS streamlining and quarterly reporting before the April 7th deadline: [1:56:52].',32,'2026-03-20 09:58:29','2026-03-20 18:31:51'),(85,'tech-lead-hima-standup-fri','2026-03-16','Attendees\n\n@Yuvanesh, @Raksha Agarwal and @Rishabh Kumar\n\n:star: Summary\n\n* Sprint Progress and Tasks\n    * @Rishabh Kumar indicated that approximately 45% of sprint work is left and will be completed today [2:26].\n    * @Raksha Agarwal is working on testing the current APK and will retest features in the current sprint [6:09].\n    * The team plans to finish all current