e build process.[9:19]\n* Work Location and Availability\n    * @Mari Muthu expressed a preference for working in Bangalore, noting reduced productivity when working from home.[20:15], [20:43]\n    * @Mari Muthu will be unavailable for the next two days, which impacts sprint planning.[2:10]\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @Mari Muthu to complete bugs 177-180 today.[4:33]\n* @Mari Muthu to generate a new final production APK and AAB with an increased version number.[10:23]\n* @Yuvanesh to confirm internal testing results by Monday.[8:56]\n* Move remaining dashboard and extra tasks to next week\'s sprint.[5:38]\n* Prepare for potential return to Bangalore office for work.[20:53]',34,'2026-03-22 14:08:15','2026-03-22 14:08:15'),(87,'tech-lead-sudar-thedal-standup-fri','2026-03-16','Summary\n\n* AI Chatbot Development Concept\n    * @Yuvanesh proposed creating an advanced chatbot that acts as a comprehensive business and data analyst, capable of providing insights across multiple dashboards.: [21:05]\n    * The proposed chatbot would analyze data from Meta admin, Razerpay, and video admin panels, offering more than just statistical information.: [22:18]\n    * @Sivaperumal and @Yuvanesh discussed using GPT and open router tokens to power the chatbot\'s intelligence.: [25:06]\n    * Key features would include generating reports, answering complex business questions, and providing predictive insights about user behavior and revenue.: [33:35]\n* Project Implementation Strategy\n    * @Yuvanesh suggested breaking the chatbot development into a five-phase project with detailed planning for each stage.: [35:56]\n    * The team aims to create a tool that could potentially replace the need for a dedicated business analyst.: [19:15]\n    * Potential capabilities include analyzing ad campaigns, subscription rates, and providing comprehensive business insights.: [39:21]\n* Team Staffing and Testing\n    * @Yuvanesh expressed concerns about the current QA intern\'s performance and engagement.: [38:21]\n    * @Raksha Agarwal mentioned challenges with the tester\'s ability to write proper test cases.: [10:25]\n    * @Bala discussed potential internship arrangements, mentioning a 15-day probation period.: [38:40]\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @Sivaperumal to create a detailed project plan for the AI chatbot, breaking it down into five distinct phases.: [35:56]\n* @Yuvanesh to review and potentially reassign or address issues with the current QA intern.: [38:21]\n* Team to explore integrating GPT and open router tokens into the chatbot development.: [25:06]\n* @Raksha Agarwal to provide additional guidance and reference materials for test case writing to the intern.: [10:25]',34,'2026-03-22 14:17:47','2026-03-22 14:17:47'),(88,'ceo-hima-kpi-review','2026-03-16','Nandha: Bengali ad spend target not met because Tiyasa is not trained yet.',NULL,'2026-03-23 06:14:10','2026-03-23 06:14:10'),(89,'ceo-ayush-daily-meetup','2026-03-23','',4,'2026-03-23 06:22:58','2026-03-23 06:22:58'),(90,'product_manager-daily-standup-dhanush-tue','2026-03-23','In dashboard trails count\'s mis match\n\n:handshake: Attendees\n\n@Bala and @Dhanush\n\n:star: Summary\n\n* Performance Metrics\n    * @Bala confirmed 16 trial registrations on the previous day (line 143). [4:22]\n    * The platform achieved 3 premium conversions, indicating potential user monetization. [4:50]\n    * Video watch counts were discussed, with specific attention to business-related metrics. [4:57]\n* Content Creation Strategy\n    * Plans to generate scripts for video content and create corresponding thumbnails. [6:51]\n    * @Dhanush suggested exploring diverse content categories, including product reviews and educational content. [8:16]\n    * The team aims to create content targeting specific audience segments, such as exam preparation and professional development. [9:47]\n* Marketing and Expansion\n    * @Dhanush proposed increasing content spend to explore new categories and expand audience reach. [13:40]\n    * Discussion of strategic content placement to maximize user engagement and platform growth. [14:23]\n    * Monthly review and planning of content strategy and marketing investments. [15:26]\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @Bala to review daily book performance and track 50% daily growth metrics. [13:20]\n* @Dhanush to develop content for new categories, focusing on professional and educational themes. [9:47]\n* Team to conduct monthly content and marketing strategy review, analyzing spending and user engagement. [15:26]\n* Explore multilingual content creation to expand platform reach. [11:15]\n\n\n\n* App Usage and Performance Metrics\n    * @Dhanush reviewed recent view statistics across different content categories, noting 37 views in one category, 154 views for business-related content, and 153 views for earning money sections [13:30].\n    * The platform appears to track user interactions, with a focus on content categories like business ideas, part-time income, and money-earning opportunities [13:39].\n* User Engagement Strategy\n    * @Dhanush emphasized a strategic focus on part-time income opportunities as a key driver for app usage and user retention [11:47].\n    * The discussion highlighted the importance of increasing app usage, user reputation, and providing valuable content for potential part-time workers [12:33].\n* Trial and Premium User Insights\n    * @Dhanush discussed the trial period strategy, suggesting that users who register and stay for 5-6 years might be more likely to become premium users [14:11].\n    * The platform is exploring ways to convert trial users to premium users by offering additional features and opportunities [14:39].\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @Dhanush to continue analyzing app usage statistics and content performance across different categories [15:11].\n* @Bala to investigate and verify premium user conversion rates and trial user engagement [17:39].\n* Review and potentially enhance content for business ideas, part-time income, and earning money sections to improve user engagement [15:00].',2,'2026-03-23 08:42:16','2026-03-24 07:21:13'),(91,'product_manager-daily-standup-tamil-tue','2026-03-23','Need to track trail taken user how many of you  completed mock test - focused\nI’ll change the current recovery screen to a proper dialog-style popup on top of the paywall , in both paywall flows.\n\n\n:handshake: Attendees\n\n@Tamil and @Bala\n\n:star: Summary\n\n* App Registration and User Metrics\n    * @Bala discussed having between 300-400 registered users in the current period [8:35].\n    * The team is tracking user registration rates and considering strategies for converting free trial users to premium users [9:23].\n    * Registration timing was noted as occurring on specific dates, including a Sunday at 3:38 [10:46].\n* Application Features\n    * The application includes configurable display modes, specifically a light mode and dark mode [6:52].\n    * @Tamil mentioned reviewing and potentially updating the payment screen and notification systems [4:37].\n    * There are discussions about implementing a premium tier with different user access levels [7:08].\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @Tamil to review and potentially modify the app\'s registration process to improve user conversion rates [8:53].\n* @Bala to analyze the current free trial to premium conversion metrics [9:24].\n* Team to evaluate the current notification and payment screen designs for potential improvements [4:37].',2,'2026-03-23 08:59:45','2026-03-23 10:05:45'),(92,'full-stack-dev-astro-standup-tue','2026-03-23','Summary\n\n* Website Accessibility\n    * @Rishabh Kumar attempted to share a website link with @Barkha Agarwal, but the site was not loading [2:05]\n    * Both participants confirmed the website was not opening successfully [3:51][4:24]\n* Next Steps\n    * @Rishabh Kumar instructed @Barkha Agarwal to check all website features and verify everything is working correctly [4:31]\n    * Plan is to reconnect after initial review to discuss any necessary changes [4:31]',35,'2026-03-23 13:13:52','2026-03-23 13:13:52'),(93,'marketing-standup-daily-tue','2026-03-23','Summary\n\n* Snapchat Advertising Challenges\n    * @Anirudh noted that low daily ad spend (₹2000-3000) might make conversions invisible in the dashboard, potentially leading to premature campaign abandonment.[4:43]\n    * The team considered alternative tracking methods, potentially using Firebase to pull events and improve campaign visibility.[5:14]\n* Ad Platform Performance\n    * Daily ad spend breakdown: Meta at ₹8,160 and Google at approximately ₹34,000-35,000.[13:30], [13:37]\n    * Language-specific performance metrics were analyzed, with variations across Tamil (1,382 registrations), Malayalam (721), Telugu (1,347), and other regional languages.[22:08], [21:53], [21:51]\n* Targeting Strategies\n    * @Anirudh suggested experimenting with different targeting approaches, including look-alike audiences and potentially exploring detailed targeting (DT) with a small budget.[19:08]\n    * The team discussed focusing on regional languages rather than Hindi, noting more potential in regional markets.[20:50], [21:02]\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @Anirudh to investigate Snapchat ad tracking methods, potentially using Firebase for event tracking.[5:14]\n* Experiment with small-budget detailed targeting (DT) campaigns to assess performance compared to open targeting strategies.[19:08]\n* Continue analyzing and optimizing language-specific ad campaigns, with a focus on regional language performance.[22:08]',3,'2026-03-24 06:18:23','2026-03-24 06:18:23'),(94,'ops-standup-daily-tue','2026-03-23','* Daily Performance Metrics\n    * @Ranjini reported 143 tickets and 40 onboarding tasks at 1:30 PM. [0:19]\n    * @Reshma Reshma reported 23 onboarding tickets, 625 total tickets, 25 specific tickets, 17 chat interactions, and 13 calls. [1:48]\n    * @Gousia reported 62 onboarding tickets, 135 total tickets, 30 \"what\'s\" tickets, and 82 Hindi onboarding tickets. [2:14]\n* Payment Verification Process\n    * @Sneha Sunoj clarified that if a dashboard shows a payment as \"paid\", it should be considered processed, and users should be advised to check with their bank for any transaction discrepancies. [5:17]\n    * For persistent payment queries, team members should collect creator ID and phone number to verify with internal team. [5:43]\n    * The team should only escalate payment issues if there\'s clear evidence of a problem. [7:48]\n* Support Ticket Challenges\n    * @Reshma Reshma reported an issue where some creators experience 24-hour app restrictions even after onboarding and taking calls. [8:58]\n    * @Ranjini highlighted ongoing problems with AI ticket responses, with some tickets remaining unresolved despite multiple interactions. [12:22]\n    * @Sneha Sunoj specified that certain ticket types (call amounts, dual detection, recharge issues) should be immediately redirected to manual support. [14:27]\n\nAction items\n\n* @Sneha Sunoj will investigate why AI tickets are not being properly redirected to manual support. [15:30]\n* @Reshma Reshma to provide screenshots of creators experiencing 24-hour app restrictions. [9:56]\n* @Ranjini to compile a list of tickets that need manual support redirection. [13:07]\n* @Gousia must complete pending Bengali language work. [2:43]\n* Team to verify and document the process for handling repeated ticket submissions. [15:01]',5,'2026-03-24 06:40:49','2026-03-24 06:40:49'),(95,'ceo-ai-standup-tue','2026-03-23','about continue sprint for fida and snehacreating spirnt  told her to focus ui and create one good character',1,'2026-03-24 06:55:47','2026-03-24 06:55:47'),(96,'cmo-anindita-daily-standup-tue','2026-03-23','Attendees\n\n@Nandha, @Anindita and @Krishnan Krishnan\n\n:star: Summary\n\n* One-Minute Free Call Strategy\n    * @Anindita proposed a strategy of offering one-minute free audio/video calls to encourage users to convert to paid users [0:32].\n    * The strategy has previously been successful in Kannada and Malayalam languages, helping increase conversion from registered to paid users [3:28].\n    * @Nandha and @Anindita agreed to focus specifically on one-minute free audio calls, which require fewer coins and are more cost-effective [5:33].\n* User Notification Strategy\n    * @Anindita suggested creating more personalized, human-like notifications instead of purely AI-generated content [18:44].\n    * The team plans to develop different notification approaches for new users, paid users, and inactive users [14:42].\n    * Notifications should aim to make users feel valued and encourage them to try the platform [13:26].\n* Creator Onboarding Challenges\n    * The team is experiencing difficulty attracting female creators, with current ads generating 60% male leads [30:42].\n    * @Nandha plans to use static posters with clear messaging targeting only female creators [31:51].\n    * @Anindita suggested including explicit language in creatives to discourage male registrations [32:07].\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @Anindita will contact Sneha to understand the current notification structure and develop a strategy for Bengali users [21:04].\n* @Nandha will talk to Bala about implementing the one-minute free audio call offer [21:27].\n* @Nandha will create targeted creatives specifically for female creator onboarding [32:04].\n* Adjust the conversion rate target from 20% to 16-17% for the initial week [23:37].\n* @Nandha will handle communication with the new social media manager [22:27].',3,'2026-03-24 07:33:57','2026-03-24 07:33:57'),(97,'ceo-hima-kpi-review','2026-03-23','Summary\n\n* Market Performance and Conversion Challenges\n    * @J P highlighted significant conversion rate challenges in Bengali and Hindi markets, with paid user percentages as low as 9-10% compared to higher performing South Indian languages [48:32].\n    * The team identified key issues including limited creator availability and low user engagement in new language markets [1:09:57].\n    * @Anindita suggested introducing more culturally relevant and clear creatives to build trust and improve conversion rates [53:17].\n* Technical Development and User Engagement\n    * The team demonstrated the newly integrated Ludo game as a strategy to increase user engagement and call duration [2:05:05].\n    * Technical improvements include a new creator scoring system based on call connection performance [1:42:37].\n    * Plans to launch an iOS app within two weeks were discussed [2:06:02].\n* Creator Onboarding and Support\n    * @Sneha Sunoj reported starting Bengali creator onboarding, with initial focus on verifying and expanding the creator base [44:42].\n    * The team discussed implementing a structured warning system for creators with automatic and manual intervention levels [1:28:17].\n    * Potential strategies include offering incentives for weekend and extended work to support onboarding [1:58:14].\n* Management Philosophy\n    * @J P emphasized a management approach focused on target achievement rather than micromanagement [1:57:18].\n    * Encouragement of continuous learning and self-improvement, especially for young team members [2:01:57].\n    * Commitment to flexible work arrangements and scaling the company strategically [1:52:00].\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @Anindita and @Nandha to develop more culturally relevant and clear creatives for Bengali and Hindi markets [53:17].\n* @Sneha Sunoj to continue expanding Bengali creator base and implement more systematic onboarding processes [44:42].\n* Technical team to finalize iOS app development within two weeks [2:06:02].\n* @Rishabh Kumar to complete dashboard improvements and address performance issues [1:23:15].\n* Team to develop a structured creator warning system with automatic and manual intervention levels [1:28:17].\n* @Anindita to investigate and resolve inconsistencies in conversion rate calculations [1:33:40].',2,'2026-03-24 07:49:31','2026-03-24 07:49:50'),(98,'cfo-stand-up-meeting-tue','2026-03-23',':headphones: Huddle notes: 24/03/2026 with @Ayush Agarwal and @ShoyabSlack AI took notes for this huddle from 13:07:19 - 13:25:21 GMT+5:30. A detailed financial discussion between a manager and an accountant focusing on tax deductions, payment reconciliation, and upcoming financial meetings, with emphasis on resolving outstanding accounting issues. View huddle in channel\n\n:handshake: Attendees\n\n@Shoyab and @Ayush Agarwal\n\n:star: Summary\n\n* TDS and Payment Collection Status\n    * @Shoyab identified discrepancies in TDS notices, with 155 inoperative PANs in Q2 reported versus 123 in their current report [8:46].\n    * Payments from key vendors like Google, Facebook, and Cashfree are pending, with some collection challenges [11:34].\n    * Some PAN numbers are inoperative and require verification before further processing [9:10].\n* Financial Reconciliation Process\n    * @Shoyab is manually reviewing bank statements and transactions, filtering and cross-checking entries to ensure accurate ledger maintenance [7:41].\n    * The reconciliation process is expected to take approximately 4-5 days, involving detailed examination of bank entries and transaction routes [7:41].\n    * Payment gateways are being separately tracked to improve financial transparency and tracking [5:23].\n* Upcoming Meetings and Follow-ups\n    * A CFO meeting is scheduled to discuss payroll slips, reconciliation of Zoho and Tally books, and TDS-related matters [3:30].\n    * @Ayush Agarwal may potentially join the CFO meeting if time permits [16:05].\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @Shoyab to complete PAN number verification and prepare a final report on inoperative PANs [9:28].\n* @Shoyab to follow up with Google regarding pending signed agreements for payments [11:50].\n* @Shoyab to conduct reconciliation of bank entries for February and March, with a focus on tracking vendor credits and debits [7:12].\n* @Shoyab to prepare for CFO meeting, focusing on payroll slips and book reconciliation [3:30].\n* @Shoyab to send final copy of PAN-related documentation today [14:34].',32,'2026-03-24 07:55:15','2026-03-24 08:10:19'),(99,'qa-daily-standup-raksha-laxmi','2026-03-23','Worked on testing the Ludo feature in the Hi Ma app, ensuring smooth gameplay during calls without affecting audio/video functionality.',36,'2026-03-24 13:05:42','2026-03-25 18:07:03'),(100,'ops-standup-daily-wed','2026-03-23','* Daily Performance Metrics\n    * @Deeksha reported 21 tickets, 68 onboarding entries, and 6 queries for the previous day [1:04].\n    * @Reshma Reshma confirmed 26 tickets, 19 onboarding entries, and 88 WhatsApp calls [1:35].\n    * @Gousia provided additional metrics including 89 total tickets, 56 user verifications across different language segments [1].\n* Technical Wallet Recharge Issue\n    * @Reshma Reshma raised a concern about users experiencing problems with wallet recharges, where money is deducted but coins are not reflecting in the user\'s account [4:59].\n    * @Sneha Sunoj suggested potential network-related issues and recommended users try uninstalling and reinstalling the app or checking on another device [6:11].\n    * The technical team claims no problem on their end, requiring further investigation [5:39].\n\nAction items\n\n* @Sneha Sunoj requested @Reshma Reshma to provide screenshots and user ID for the wallet recharge issue [5:31].\n* Team to work on improving user ratings as emphasized by @Sneha Sunoj [4:35].\n* Investigate the persistent wallet recharge problem, potentially involving technical team for deeper analysis',5,'2026-03-25 06:08:56','2026-03-25 06:08:56'),(101,'product_manager-daily-standup-tamil-wed','2026-03-23',':star: Summary\n\n* Marketing and Advertising Spend\n    * @Bala discussed budget increases and spending patterns in 