5:04'),(121,'marketing-standup-daily-fri','2026-03-23',':headphones: Huddle notes: 27/03/2026 with @Nandha and @AnirudhSlack AI took notes for this huddle from 11:35:19 - 11:58:30 GMT+5:30. Performance marketing discussion between @Nandha and @Anirudh focusing on campaign metrics, ad spend across different languages, and creative strategies for digital advertising. View huddle in channel\n\n:handshake: Attendees\n\n@Nandha, @Anirudh and @Krishnan Krishnan\n\n:star: Summary\n\n* Campaign Performance Metrics\n    * @Nandha and @Anirudh reviewed total campaign spend of 7.55 lakhs across multiple languages [1:34].\n    * Language-wise spend breakdown was analyzed, with Telugu showing the highest spend at 2.16 lakhs and Bengali the lowest at 6.96k [5:59][6:04].\n    * Discussed registration metrics across different languages, with Telugu having 12,366 registrations and Malayalam 7,782 [7:15][7:09].\n* Campaign Structure and Creative Strategy\n    * @Nandha proposed running campaigns with 100-200 creatives, suggesting a more diverse creative approach [7:39].\n    * Discussion around separating ad groups and creating multiple asset sets for different targeting strategies [8:27].\n    * @Anirudh raised concerns about potentially needing to restructure current creative approaches [9:18].\n* Creator and Spending Analysis\n    * @Anirudh suggested tracking creator-specific spending separately, particularly for female creators [11:20].\n    * Discussed the importance of targeting and analyzing creator-focused ad spending [11:06].\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @Nandha to conduct interviews for Malayalam language content creators [16:00].\n* @Anirudh to review and potentially restructure current campaign creative strategies [9:18].\n* Team to analyze detailed breakdown of creator-specific ad spending across different language segments [11:20].',3,'2026-03-27 06:46:36','2026-03-27 06:46:36'),(122,'product_manager-daily-standup-dhanush-fri','2026-03-23','Summary\n\n* Platform Performance Metrics\n    * @Dhanush reported 89 new registrations and 16 trial participants for the previous day [1:31].\n    * Premium conversion count was zero for the day [1:39].\n    * New video watch accounts totaled 68, with top performing categories being Business Ideas (39 accounts) and Earn Money (29 accounts) [3:34].\n* Content Creation Strategy\n    * @Dhanush outlined plans to upload one video, coordinate with content creators, and collect customer reviews [4:39].\n    * Discussion included poster design, script writing, and content creation coordination [5:00].\n    * Challenges were noted around script writing and content creation consistency [11:51].\n* Work Opportunities\n    * @Dhanush discussed potential work opportunities targeting various demographics including college students, housewives, and job seekers [9:55].\n    * The platform aims to provide flexible work options with varying time commitments [9:16].\n    * Goal is to create income opportunities for individuals with different backgrounds and availability [10:18].\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @Dhanush will upload one video today [4:39].\n* @Dhanush to coordinate with content creators for poster design and script writing [5:00].\n* Collect customer reviews and feedback to improve platform offerings [4:39].\n* Review and optimize content creation process, particularly script writing [11:51].',2,'2026-03-27 06:52:49','2026-03-27 06:52:49'),(123,'cmo-anindita-daily-standup-fri','2026-03-23',':headphones: Huddle notes: 27/03/2026 with @Nandha and @AninditaSlack AI took notes for this huddle from 12:25:42 - 13:39:33 GMT+5:30. The team discussed strategies to improve user conversion rates for the Bengali language version of their app, focusing on addressing a significant drop in user purchases after implementing a free coin offer. View huddle in channel\n\n:handshake: Attendees\n\n@Nandha, @Anindita, @Sneha Sunoj and @Bala\n\n:star: Summary\n\n* Conversion Rate Problem\n    * @Anindita observed that the conversion rate dropped dramatically from 12.9% to 6% after introducing a free first-minute call offer.[0:53]\n    * The team hypothesized that users who get a free first call and dislike the creator are unlikely to make subsequent purchases.[5:55]\n    * Current average paying amount in Bengali is around 80-117 rupees, indicating price sensitivity.[36:27]\n* Proposed Solutions\n    * Immediately discontinue the free coin offer to stop further conversion rate decline.[11:28]\n    * Implement a \"trigger call\" mechanism where new users receive a fake incoming call that redirects them to purchase coins.[46:31]\n    * Change the default coin package to 129 rupees, which aligns with user spending patterns.[1:00:41]\n    * Develop personalized push notifications to engage potential users.[1:07:48]\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @Bala to check with technical team about implementing the trigger call mechanism.[1:07:38]\n* @Sneha Sunoj to prepare personalized push notifications for Bengali users over the next 2-3 days.[1:07:48]\n* @Nandha to modify the default coin package to 129 rupees.[1:08:33]\n* Team to review conversion rates by Monday to assess the effectiveness of these strategies.[1:08:48]',3,'2026-03-27 08:18:35','2026-03-27 08:18:35'),(124,'cmo-creative-team-daily-standup-fri','2026-03-23',':headphones: Huddle notes: 27/03/2026 with @Nandha and @Krishnan KrishnanSlack AI took notes for this huddle from 13:40:53 - 13:48:00 GMT+5:30. A team meeting involving creative professionals discussing video production, with fragmented communication and multiple language switches. View huddle in channel\n\n:handshake: Attendees\n\n@Nandha, @Krishnan Krishnan, @Sooraj and @anas\n\n:star: Summary\n\n* Video Production Planning\n    * @Krishnan Krishnan suggested generating 4 videos during the meeting [2:06].\n    * The team discussed scheduling, with @Sooraj mentioning a 2:30 time slot [2:28].\n* Team Communication\n    * The conversation was characterized by brief, often incomplete statements across multiple languages.\n    * Participants seemed to understand each other despite the fragmented communication style.\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @Krishnan Krishnan to lead video generation process for 4 videos [2:12].\n* Team to reconvene at 2:30 to discuss further video production details [2:39].',3,'2026-03-27 08:41:29','2026-03-27 08:41:29'),(125,'product_manager-daily-standup-tamil-fri','2026-03-23','Summary\n\n* Performance Metrics\n    * @Bala reported a completion rate of 6.17% in some category [10:19].\n    * Subject law was identified as the most viewed category [10:55].\n    * Discussions involved tracking performance levels and metrics across different categories [11:45].\n* Platform Testing\n    * Participants discussed screen sharing functionality, with some technical challenges noted [3:37].\n    * Testing processes and monitoring were briefly mentioned, suggesting ongoing platform development [1:21].\n* Performance Levels\n    * @Tamil referenced multiple performance levels, including Level 1, Level 242, and Level Ramao [6:03].\n    * Discussions indicated tracking of user or content performance across different levels [7:06].\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @Bala to review and potentially adjust performance tracking metrics across different categories [11:45].\n* Investigate and resolve screen sharing technical issues [3:37].\n* Continue monitoring platform performance levels and user engagement [6:03].',2,'2026-03-27 09:07:39','2026-03-27 09:08:47'),(126,'tech-lead-hima-standup','2026-03-23','Attendees\n\n@Yuvanesh, @Rishabh Kumar and @Raksha Agarwal\n\n:star: Summary\n\n* Sprint Completion\n    * @Yuvanesh indicated the current sprint is over and proposed moving to the next sprint\'s tasks. [5:02]\n    * @Raksha Agarwal was asked to review and approve remaining items within 30 minutes. [4:42]\n    * The team agreed to move unresolved bugs to the next sprint\'s backlog. [4:50]\n* Marketing Dashboard Development\n    * @Yuvanesh wants to develop a new marketing dashboard based on requirements from Nanda. [5:30]\n    * Required metrics include DAU, MAU, ARPU, open rate, conversion rate, new user purchases, total registrations, and verified users. [7:48]\n    * @Rishabh Kumar suggested creating a new \"Marketing\" menu to house these dashboard metrics. [8:43]\n    * Performance issues were noted, with JP reporting slow dashboard loading times. [6:04]\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @Rishabh Kumar to clarify specific marketing dashboard metrics with the team. [8:58]\n* @Rishabh Kumar to prepare a document estimating implementation time for the marketing dashboard. [9:42]\n* @Yuvanesh to create a new marketing dashboard menu. [8:38]\n* Team to investigate and resolve dashboard performance issues. [6:04]\n* Bugs from current sprint to be moved to next sprint\'s backlog. [4:50]',34,'2026-03-30 02:18:13','2026-03-30 02:18:13'),(127,'tech-lead-hima-standup-tue','2026-03-23',':headphones: Huddle notes: 24/03/2026 with @Rishabh Kumar and @YuvaneshSlack AI took notes for this huddle from 12:37:03 - 13:22:00 GMT+5:30. The meeting focused on establishing a structured workflow for bug fixing, testing, and software development, with a particular emphasis on onboarding a new team member and preparing for an upcoming release. View huddle in channel\n\n:handshake: Attendees\n\n@Yuvanesh, @Rishabh Kumar, @Bala, @Sivaperumal and @Raksha Agarwal\n\n:star: Summary\n\n* Bug Fixing and Testing Workflow\n    * @Yuvanesh outlined a detailed process where @Sivaperumal will fix approximately 10 bugs per day, with @Raksha Agarwal responsible for testing those fixes.\n    * The team will coordinate to ensure bugs are comprehensively tested, with a goal of completing and validating fixes by Thursday night.\n    * @Raksha Agarwal expressed concern about needing to test not just specific bug fixes, but also ensure overall app functionality remains intact.\n* Technical Onboarding\n    * @Rishabh Kumar provided detailed guidance to @Sivaperumal on Git repository management, including how to create and manage branches.\n    * The team emphasized the importance of creating separate branches for different work items and pushing code before switching branches.\n    * Instructions were given on how to move tasks through different stages (in progress, review, ready for QA) in their project management system.\n* Release Preparation\n    * The team plans to have a release-ready APK by Friday evening.\n    * Multiple team members will review and test the APK, with @Raksha Agarwal conducting comprehensive testing across different modules.\n    * Future work will include implementing star creator features and bonus features.\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @Sivaperumal to fix approximately 10 bugs daily and create separate Git branches for each work item.\n* @Raksha Agarwal to test bug fixes and ensure overall app functionality remains stable.\n* @Rishabh Kumar will review and merge branches after bug fixes are completed.\n* Team to prepare release-ready APK by Friday evening for final review.\n* @Sivaperumal to document test cases for each bug fix to assist @Raksha Agarwal in testing.',34,'2026-03-30 02:18:57','2026-03-30 02:18:57'),(128,'tech-lead-hima-standup-wed','2026-03-23','Attendees\n\n@Rishabh Kumar, @Yuvanesh, @Raksha Agarwal and @Sivaperumal\n\n:star: Summary\n\n* APK Testing Challenges\n    * @Raksha Agarwal reported significant issues installing the APK on a tablet, with audio not working during calls [3:03].\n    * @Rishabh Kumar noted that Lakshmi was unable to install the universal APK, suggesting potential device compatibility problems [4:28].\n    * The team identified audio call disconnection as a critical issue that must be resolved before further testing [4:02].\n* Testing Strategy\n    * @Yuvanesh suggested focusing on rural testing first and then addressing specific technical issues [3:46].\n    * The team agreed to collaborate on resolving connectivity problems before proceeding with comprehensive testing [4:17].\n* Team Task Allocation\n    * @Yuvanesh recommended that @Raksha Agarwal and @Sivaperumal work together on testing and feature development [6:15].\n    * @Yuvanesh instructed team members to communicate APK readiness and testing progress in their group chat [5:37].\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @Raksha Agarwal to continue troubleshooting APK installation and audio call connectivity issues [3:27].\n* @Sivaperumal to assist @Raksha Agarwal with testing and then focus on resolving bugs [6:40].\n* Team to document and share detailed findings about APK and audio call problems [6:04].\n* @Rishabh Kumar to investigate the specific device (tablet) causing installation difficulties [4:47].',34,'2026-03-30 02:19:38','2026-03-30 02:19:38'),(129,'tech-lead-hima-standup-thu','2026-03-23','Attendees\n\n@Yuvanesh, @Rishabh Kumar, @Sivaperumal and @Raksha Agarwal\n\n:star: Summary\n\n* Sprint Progress and Task Distribution\n    * @Rishabh Kumar reported ongoing technical challenges, particularly with FCM issues that prevented testing from proceeding smoothly [9:49].\n    * @Yuvanesh proposed a detailed task breakdown, requesting @Sivaperumal to complete 23 bugs and @Raksha Agarwal to test 10 bugs [11:03].\n    * The team agreed to have a follow-up call at 5:30 PM to review progress, particularly for Ludo feature testing [15:49].\n* Technical Features Under Development\n    * @Rishabh Kumar highlighted several features in progress: Automatic Bonus feature, tracking link with some issues, and video call functionality [6:21].\n    * Ludo feature testing requires connection and coordination between team members [5:35].\n    * Some technical obstacles, like FCM and call connectivity, are impeding smooth feature development [9:49].\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @Sivaperumal to complete 23 bugs by end of day [11:03].\n* @Raksha Agarwal to complete 10 bugs and Ludo feature testing [12:57].\n* @Rishabh Kumar to continue working on tracking link and video call features [6:21].\n* Team to reconvene at 5:30 PM for progress review and Ludo testing [15:49].',34,'2026-03-30 02:22:22','2026-03-30 02:22:22'),(130,'tech-lead-hima-standup-fri','2026-03-23','Attendees\n\n@Rishabh Kumar, @Yuvanesh, @Raksha Agarwal and @Sivaperumal\n\n:star: Summary\n\n* Sprint Completion and Testing\n    * @Rishabh Kumar confirmed that his side of work is completed and is ready for testing [3:03].\n    * The team planned to have @Raksha Agarwal test the APK with major test cases after @Rishabh Kumar merges the code from @Sivaperumal [6:21].\n    * The goal is to complete all test cases by evening and resolve any potential conflicts immediately [6:50].\n* Ludo App and Technical Issues\n    * @Raksha Agarwal reported audio call connectivity problems that need resolution [5:43].\n    * The team agreed to spend 15-20 minutes after the meeting to troubleshoot Ludo app connectivity [6:07].\n    * Testing of Ludo app will focus on important features like starred items and automatic bonus functionality [6:42].\n* Sprint Planning and Task Management\n    * @Yuvanesh mentioned planning a follow-up call to discuss the next sprint and ensure clarity for all team members [8:10].\n    * Some unfinished tasks from the current sprint will be moved to the next sprint [10:14].\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @Rishabh Kumar to merge code from @Sivaperumal and create a combined APK for testing [6:21].\n* @Raksha Agarwal to perform comprehensive testing of the APK, focusing on major test cases [7:51].\n* Team to troubleshoot Ludo app and audio call connectivity issues within 15-20 minutes after the meeting [6:07].\n* @Yuvanesh to prepare for a sprint planning call to discuss next steps and task allocation [8:10].\n* Unresolved tasks from current sprint to be moved to next sprint [10:14].',34,'2026-03-30 02:22:51','2026-03-30 02:22:51'),(131,'tech-lead-onlycare-standup','2026-03-23','Attendees\n\n@Yuvanesh and @Mari Muthu\n\n:star: Summary\n\n* Work Arrangement\n    * @Yuvanesh confirmed a flexible work-from-home policy with no fixed working hours [1:00].\n    * The primary requirement is availability for meetings and being responsive to calls [1:06].\n    * The team\'s primary goal is completing assigned tasks within one week [1:23].\n* Current Project Status\n    * @Mari Muthu discovered a bug in the app\'s registration process, specifically affecting female user registration [2:04].\n    * Male user registration email triggering works correctly [2:04].\n    * Two primary issues identified: SDK problem and ringtone not playing on Android 12+ devices [3:49].\n* Release Plan\n    * @Yuvanesh wants to release the app today, despite minor bugs [2:50].\n    * Plan is to fix issues by 3:30-4:00 PM, with testing by 4:00 PM [4:28].\n    * Aim to complete release by 6:00 PM today [4:34].\n* Next Sprint Planning\n    * Current sprint covers 53.5 hours with 36 tasks [5:37].\n    * KYC withdrawal feature is active and ready for integration [6:02].\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @Mari Muthu to fix minor registration bugs by 4:00 PM [0:40].\n* @Mari Muthu to resolve SDK and ringtone issues on Android 12+ devices [3:49].\n* @Mari Muthu to integrate KYC withdrawal feature by 5:00 PM [6:52].\n* Team to prepare for app release by 6:00 PM today [4:34].\n* Plan next sprint after completing current release tasks [7:04].',34,'2026-03-30 03:44:43','2026-03-30 03:44:43'),(132,'tech-lead-onlycare-standup-tue','2026-03-23','Attendees\n\n@Yuvanesh and @Mari Muthu\n\n:star: Summary\n\n* Sprint Progress and Release Planning\n    * @Mari Muthu is working on resolving bugs identified in the current sprint, aiming to complete them by tomorrow. [0:41]\n    * The team is preparing for a release on Friday, which will include SDK full integration, true colors implementation, and balance changes. [2:18][2:30]\n    * Sprint items from 193 to 207 need to be moved and completed. [1:59]\n* KYC Activation Process\n    * @Yuvanesh instructed @Mari Muthu to contact Kaset and document step-by-step requirements for KYC activation. [2:53]\n    * Current understanding is that adding a bank account is a prerequisite for transferring money to users. [3:00]\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @Mari Muthu to complete sprint bugs by tomorrow. [0:41]\n* @Mari Muthu to contact Kaset and document detailed KYC activation steps, then send to @Yuvanesh. [2:53]\n* @Yuvanesh will forward KYC activation steps to Para for implementation by Friday. [3:03]\n* Prepare for Friday release with SDK integration, true colors, and balance changes. [2:18][2:30]\n* Move and complete sprint items from 193 to 207. [1:59]',34,'2026-03-30 03:46:13','2026-03-30 03:46:13'),(133,'tech-lead-onlycare-standup-wed','2026-03-23','Attendees\n\n@Mari Muthu and @Yuvanesh\n\n:star: Summary\n\n* Project Status and Testing\n    * @Mari Muthu confirmed that testing for the registration event is complete: [0:43]\n    * @Yuvanesh verified that the system is working and ready to proceed: [0:48], [0:52]\n* Payout Integration and Release Planning\n    * @Mari Muthu reported that Mbala instructed him to complete end-to-end payout integration before distributing real money at production level: [2:15]\n    * The team plans to release a new version on Friday, incorporating Google SDK and payout integration: [2:58], [3:06]\n* Communication Strategy\n    * @Yuvanesh plans to create a Slack group to improve team communication and visibility: [3:21]\n\nAction items\n\n* @Mari Muthu to complete full payout integration before Friday: [2:51]\n* @Yuvanesh to create a new Slack group for team communication: [3:21]\n* Prepare for software release on Friday, including Google SDK implementation: [2:58]',34,'2026-03-30 03:46:58','2026-03-30 03:46:58'),(134,'tech-lead-onlycare-standup-thu','2026-03-23','Attendees\n\n@Yuvanesh and @Mari Muthu\n\n:star: Summary\n\n* Travel Plans\n    * @Yuvanesh is traveling to Bangalore in the first week of April and feels uneasy about being alone in the office.[1:13]\n    * @Mari Muthu is traveling to Bangalore tomorrow with a train at 5 PM and needs permission from work.[1:26]\n* Work Arrangements\n    * Both @Yuvanesh and @Mari Muthu are comfortable with work from home arrangements.[3:35]\n    * Previous discussions with Perumal and JP about work arrangements have been resolved.[4:09]\n* Project Status\n    * The app development is completed, with only integration remaining.[4:31]\n    * Integration testing revealed a need to add a funding source before final testing.[4:38]\n    * Plan to conduct real payment testing in the evening and involve Bala for money transfer.[4:59]\n* Accommodation\n    * @Yuvanesh has already vacated previous accommodation and moved belongings, paying extra for transportation.[1:56], [2:08]\n    * Discussing a new accommodation arrangement on a daily payment basis.[2:54]\nAction items\n\n* @Mari Muthu to complete remaining design and integration tasks today.[3:26]\n* @Mari Muthu to add funding source for project testing.[4:42]\n* @Yuvanesh to arrange money transfer for testing with Bala.[5:20]\n* Conduct real payment testing this evening.[4:59]\n* @Mari Muthu to finalize tasks before traveling to Bangalore tomorrow.[5:34]',34,'2026-03-30 03:49:44','2026-03-30 03:49:44'),(135,'tech-lead-onlycare-standup-fri','2026-03-23','Attendees\n\n@Yuvanesh and @Mari Muthu\n\n:star: Summary\n\n* Payout System Integration\n    * @Mari Muthu confirmed that the payout system is fully integrated but requires testing with real money amounts [0:18].\n    * @Yuvanesh agreed to proceed with testing the system next week [0:29].\n* Admin Panel Dashboard\n    * @Mari Muthu mentioned that some sections of the admin panel dashboard need completion [0:41].\n    * @Yuvanesh acknowledged the dashboard work and indicated it would be addressed after the current task [0:48].\n* Financial and Contact Information\n    * Discussion involved verifying bank account details and contact information [1:13].\n    * @Yuvanesh indicated some hesitation or complexity around sharing bank details [1:27].\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @Yuvanesh to test payout system with real money amounts next week [0:29].\n* @Mari Muthu to complete remaining sections in the admin panel dashboard [0:41].\n* Verify and finalize bank account and contact information for the system [1:13].',34,'2026-03-30 03:50:05','2026-03-30 03:50:05'),(136,'cfo-stand-up-meeting','2026-03-30','Slack AI took notes for this huddle from 18:24:15 - 20:13:44 GMT+5:30. A detailed discussion between a finance executive and senior management about payroll calculations, salary structures, and accounting processes, focusing on implementing standardized methods and using Zoho accounting software. View huddle in channel\n\n:handshake: Attendees\n\n@Shoyab and @Ayush Agarwal\n\n:star: Summary\n\n* Payroll and Salary Calculations\n    * @Shoyab explained the complexity of calculating Cost to Company (CTC) and performing reverse calculations for employees, highlighting variations in salary components like basic pay, HRA, and statutory contributions. [3:20]\n    * The team discussed the need to standardize salary structures across employees, particularly for PF and ESIC calculations. [49:09]\n    * They agreed to use a consistent approach where CTC is divided into fixed components, with careful consideration of the ₹21,000 threshold for ESIC applicability. [35:49]\n* Accounting and Expense Categorization\n    * @Shoyab explained the challenges with Zoho accounting software, particularly in categorizing and matching invoices and payments, with 696 entries being uncategorized and recategorized. [57:39]\n    * The team discussed the complexity of matching payments to specific invoices, especially for vendors like Facebook, where payment dates and invoice dates might not align perfectly. [1:06:26]\n    * They recommended a monthly reconciliation process to ensure accurate accounting and vendor payment tracking. [1:11:03]\n* Software Implementation and Process Improvement\n    * The team plans to implement Zoho payroll software to standardize salary calculations and reduce manual complexity. [30:56]\n    * @Ayush Agarwal suggested adding more tax-saving allowance columns in the payroll system to benefit employees. [50:20]\n    * They agreed to review and finalize payroll details before the 10th of each month to ensure accuracy and timely processing. [38:10]\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @Shoyab to prepare a standardized salary calculation template that can be used across all employees, considering PF, ESIC, and other statutory contributions. [56:35]\n* @Shoyab to work with the CFO to uncategorize and recategorize 696 accounting entries in the Zoho system, ensuring accurate invoice and payment matching. [58:03]\n* @Ayush Agarwal and @Shoyab to meet before the 10th of April to review and finalize payroll details for all 30-40 employees using the Zoho payroll sheet. [56:22]\n* Implement a monthly reconciliation process for vendor payments, particularly for vendors like Facebook and Google, to ensure accurate accounting. [1:11:03]',4,'2026-03-30 05:02:14','2026-03-30 14:51:31'),(137,'creative-kpi-review-20260330','2026-03-30','@Bala [0:08]: Mm\n\n@J P [0:14]: Hello\n\n@Bala [0:15]: OK\n\n@J P [0:18]: OK\n\n@Bala [0:20]: OK bro\n\n@Bala [0:59]: In 11 o\'clock we in the report.\n\n@J P [1:06]: I I don\'t remember.\n\n@Anindita [4:16]: Nah Male. Oh\n\n@J P [4:22]: I\n\n@Anindita [4:26]: Important. Let me think. Yeah we can go.\n\n@J P [4:39]: I.\n\n@Nandha [4:44]: I like it because it\n\n@J P [4:52]: They both\n\n@Nandha [4:54]: Pocket\n\n@J P [4:55]: Give it another one,\n\n@Nandha [4:56]: Hi, yes, yes, yes\n\n@J P [5:35]: 22 I need not a bitter, OK, yeah. A bitter. So tell the one, so I asked the campaign surrounding.\n\n@Nandha [5:49]: Uh, yes, bro, the campaigns are doing good.\n\n@J P [5