ization Strategy\n    * @J P proposed an auto-pay model where users pay ₹1 to enable weekly payments of ₹399, potentially increasing conversion rates [1:33:20].\n    * @Anindita expressed concerns about user experience, emphasizing the need for clear explanations and non-skippable explainer videos [1:42:03].\n    * The team agreed to implement this strategy first in the Bengali market as an experiment [1:45:46].\n* Marketing and Outreach\n    * @Ayush Agarwal suggested exploring WhatsApp marketing and hiring experts to send bulk messages to potential creators [57:12].\n    * @J P recommended targeting female job seekers and using existing user databases for outreach [59:37].\n    * The team aims to reduce customer acquisition costs while increasing creator engagement [58:23].\n* Technical Improvements\n    * @Sneha Sunoj reported ongoing issues with AI ticket resolution, noting inconsistent redirections and response accuracy [1:55:13].\n    * @Ayush Agarwal suggested implementing more robust data analysis to track creator performance and metrics [2:14:31].\n    * The team discussed adding a real-time status check for payouts through the cash-free payment system [2:04:17].\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @Sneha Sunoj to lead WhatsApp marketing efforts and connect with potential marketing agencies [1:48:39].\n* @Krishnan Krishnan to create a non-skippable explainer video for the new auto-pay model in Hindi [1:44:12].\n* @Anindita to work with the creative team on developing clear communication about the new payment model [1:41:07].\n* @Yuvanesh to investigate and resolve AI ticket routing inconsistencies [2:00:07].\n* @Ayush Agarwal to explore hiring a data analyst to provide insights on creator performance metrics [2:15:15].',2,'2026-03-31 05:59:52','2026-03-31 05:59:52'),(140,'product_manager-daily-standup-tamil-tue','2026-03-30','* Payment and Conversion Metrics\n    * @Tamil discussed trial conversion rates, noting an 8% increase in conversion numbers [21:24].\n    * The team analyzed payment patterns, including first-time, second-time, and third-time payment behaviors [21:54].\n    * Current active subscribers were reported around 40+ users, with 317 registrations per 1080 total users [20:37].\n* User Registration and Growth\n    * The team observed a monthly registration of approximately 958 trial users [26:50].\n    * @Bala highlighted that they currently have 600 registered members, with potential for growth [26:25].\n    * The platform is tracking user progression across different registration groups, with at least four distinct user groups identified [24:20].\n* Marketing and Expansion Strategies\n    * Discussion included potential marketing channels like YouTube and textbook-related promotions [25:29].\n    * The team is targeting a 10% increase in conversion and active subscriber rates [22:46].\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @Tamil to review and analyze the 8% increase in conversion rates in more detail [21:24].\n* Team to develop strategies to improve conversion from trial to premium subscriptions [22:46].\n* Continue monitoring registration trends across different user groups [24:20].',2,'2026-03-31 06:31:39','2026-03-31 06:31:39'),(141,'ops-standup-daily-tue','2026-03-30','* Daily Performance Metrics\n    * @Ranjini completed 180 tickets, 190 male cases [1:06]\n    * @Deeksha handled 1414 tickets, 27 onboarding cases, and 6 queries [1:27]\n    * @Reshma Reshma processed 12 tickets, 41 onboarding cases, 1818 WhatsApp chats, and 122 calls [1:52]\n    * @Gousia managed 30 tickets, 126 onboarding cases, 25 loss cases, and 55 Hindi cases [2:04]\n* PAN Card Linking Initiative\n    * Critical tax-related task involving 447 users with inactive/invalid PAN registrations [4:21]\n    * Team must contact users and request PAN-Aadhaar linking by April 6th [5:04]\n    * Potential financial consequences include account restrictions and potential company tax penalties [15:25]\n* Team Structural Changes\n    * @Ranjini is transitioning from support to QA [10:22]\n    * New team members Nisha (Tamil support) and Angeli (Bengali support) have recently joined [10:22]\n* Technical Support Challenges\n    * Ongoing issues with recharge page and payment processing [11:26]\n    * Dashboard experiencing errors with amount additions [13:26]\n    * Management is working with technical team to resolve these issues [12:28]\n\nAction items\n\n* @Ranjini to begin PAN card linking outreach, targeting completion by end of week [10:11]\n* All team members to focus on contacting 447 users about PAN-Aadhaar linking [10:55]\n* @Deeksha to verify and resolve dashboard amount addition errors [13:40]\n* Team to prioritize tickets, reviews, and onboarding tasks [14:08]',5,'2026-03-31 06:48:37','2026-03-31 06:48:41'),(142,'marketing-standup-daily-tue','2026-03-30',':headphones: Huddle notes: 31/03/2026 with @Nandha and @AnirudhSlack AI took notes for this huddle from 12:12:30 - 12:29:05 GMT+5:30. Performance marketing meeting between two marketers discussing detailed ad spend, campaign performance, and strategic targeting across multiple Indian languages and regions. View huddle in channel\n\n:handshake: Attendees\n\n@Nandha and @Anirudh\n\n:star: Summary\n\n* Ad Spend and Performance Metrics\n    * @Nandha and @Anirudh reviewed total ad spend across different platforms, with Google Ads at 67,000 and Meta Ads at 7,782.\n    * Language-wise performance was analyzed, including Tamil (2.93), Telugu (2.24), Kannada (1.40), and Bengali (8K).\n    * Last week\'s total ad spend was approximately 70 lakhs, with a target of around 10 lakhs per day.\n* Regional Targeting Strategy\n    * @Anirudh highlighted a focus on Hindi and Bengali markets, with specific attention to states like Uttar Pradesh.\n    * Campaign targets were discussed for various regions, including Tamil Nadu, Telugu states, and other language markets.\n    * The team is strategically adjusting targeting and spending across different lingui