e suggestions. [22:26]\n* Content and Business Strategy\n    * @Dhanush suggested focusing on interactive learning and solutions for educated and general users. [23:48]\n    * The platform aims to provide business ideas, earning opportunities, and educational content. [22:26]\n    * Discussion included plans for video uploads and content diversification. [7:33]\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @Dhanush to finalize chatbot design with interactive features by next meeting. [23:48]\n* @Bala to review and compile performance metrics for the past 2-3 weeks. [28:51]\n* Team to plan and upload new content, targeting 90 videos in the upcoming period. [27:56]\n* @Dhanush to develop comprehensive problem-solving scenarios for the chatbot. [21:35]',2,'2026-03-31 07:06:54','2026-03-31 07:06:54'),(145,'ceo-ayush-daily-meetup-tue','2026-03-30','1)Auditor discussion Chirag Dhariwal\n\n2)March Salary\n\n3)Zocket Subscription\n\n4)Books review\n\nabove ayush going to so thois wpkr',1,'2026-03-31 07:19:54','2026-03-31 07:19:54'),(146,'cmo-creative-team-daily-standup-tue','2026-03-30',':headphones: Huddle notes: 31/03/2026 with @Nandha and @Krishnan KrishnanSlack AI took notes for this huddle from 12:50:02 - 13:08:46 GMT+5:30. A team meeting discussing video production, content creation, and social media strategy, with multiple team members reviewing their current progress and upcoming tasks across various platforms. View huddle in channel\n\n:handshake: Attendees\n\n@Nandha, @Krishnan Krishnan, @anas and @Sooraj\n\n:star: Summary\n\n* Video Production Status\n    * @Krishnan Krishnan discussed progress on video generation and script delivery, indicating multiple videos are in various stages of completion [1:02].\n    * @anas mentioned working on 25 videos and needing to make adjustments to background music and editing [6:06].\n    * The team is focusing on creating videos for different categories including creator, influencer, and business content [12:59].\n* Content Distribution Strategy\n    * @Nandha outlined plans to distribute business videos across multiple platforms, with a specific focus on Instagram and community channels [14:13].\n    * The team discussed creating content for different target audiences, including individual entrepreneurs and business segments [11:35].\n    * Considerations were made about maintaining community guidelines and avoiding potential content restrictions [14:37].\n* Design and Branding\n    *  and  discussed color palette and design considerations for social media posts [15:15].\n    * The team emphasized the importance of consistent visual branding across different content types [15:35].\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n*  to complete editing on 25 videos, with specific attention to background music and video quality [6:06].\n*  to finalize Instagram poster designs and content calendar [17:57].\n*  to review and ensure videos comply with community guidelines before posting [14:37].\n* Team to develop targeted content for different platform segments: creators, influencers, and businesses [12:59].\n\nThis tool uses AI to generate notes, so some information may be inaccurate. They\'re based on the huddle transcript and thread and can be edited anytime.',3,'2026-03-31 08:22:34','2026-03-31 08:22:34'),(147,'cfo-stand-up-meeting-wed','2026-03-30','Yesterday : 1st Half Day - Zoho Payroll Software & Miscellaneous.\n\n2nd Half Day - Payroll structuring for March 2026 Salary.\n\nToday: 1. Ayush assigned tasks 2. Tally Accounting Completion, 3. Collect March 2026 Remaining bank statement - update in Tally, 4. CA Chirag Meeting, 5. Coordinate with CFO Angle, 6. TDS Certificate DSC Signed.\n\n:headphones: Huddle notes: 01/04/2026 with @Ayush Agarwal and @ShoyabSlack AI took notes for this huddle from 17:43:58 - 18:50:37 GMT+5:30. A detailed financial discussion between an accountant and a manager focusing on tax deductions, vendor reconciliation, and pending financial tasks for the end of the financial year. View huddle in channel\n\n:handshake: Attendees\n\n@Ayush Agarwal and @Shoyab\n\n:star: Summary\n\n* TDS Tracking and Reconciliation\n    * @Shoyab has prepared a comprehensive spreadsheet tracking TDS for various vendors, categorizing them by B2C and foreign vendors.[1:01:09]\n    * The team needs to cross-check TDS calculations with bank statements and finalize payments before the 30th April deadline.[14:26]\n    * Some challenges exist with incomplete invoice records and potential discrepancies in TDS deductions across different vendors.[56:58]\n* Vendor Payment Reconciliation\n    * @Ayush Agarwal suggested creating vendor reconciliation sheets in Excel, starting with major vendors like Google and Meta.[53:44]\n    * The team identified challenges with tracking payments from platforms like Agora, Karza, and Digital Ocean.[1:01:45]\n    * Some vendors have not provided complete billing information, making reconciliation difficult.[58:20]\n* Financial Software and Accounting Challenges\n    * @Shoyab noted issues with Zoho Books, finding its categorization process complex and time-consuming compared to Tally.[15:38]\n    * The team is experiencing delays with financial software updates, particularly with TDS-related platforms.[0:56]\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @Shoyab to complete vendor reconciliation in Excel, focusing on major vendors and categorizing payments.[53:13]\n* Resolve TDS payments and reconciliation before the 30th April deadline.[14:26]\n* @Ayush Agarwal to review the prepared TDS tracking spreadsheet and verify calculations.[1:01:09]\n* Follow up with vendors like Agora and Karza to obtain complete billing and payment information.[58:20]\n* Investigate and potentially resolve issues with Zoho Books\' accounting process.[15:38]',32,'2026-04-01 05:33:18','2026-04-01 14:35:25'),(148,'ops-standup-daily-wed','2026-03-30','* Daily Work Status\n    * @Ranjini completed 4 onboarding tickets in the morning, with plans to continue after lunch. [4:45]\n    * Team members reported ticket and onboarding volumes across different languages: Tamil (15 tickets), Telugu (25 tickets), Bengali (30 tickets), Hindi (27 tickets), Malayalam (6 tickets). [0:52]\n* Technical Payment Issues\n    * App experienced a technical glitch yesterday evening preventing users from purchasing coins, which has since been resolved. [7:34]\n    * Starting April 2nd, creators can only withdraw funds via bank transfer, with transactions taking approximately 24 hours to process. [8:11]\n    * @Deeksha reported 7 complaints from users unable to make payments or purchase coins. [7:33]\n* Additional Concerns\n    * @Deeksha raised concerns about poor AI response quality, suggesting the need for prompt optimization. [11:08]\n    * Some creators are experiencing issues with showing tapes but not receiving account amounts. [14:37]\n\nAction items\n\n* @Sneha Sunoj will attempt to modify AI response prompts to improve user interaction quality. [11:24]\n* Team to inform creators about new bank transfer-only withdrawal method and potential 24-hour processing time. [12:15]\n* Focus on completing PAN card verification calls across all language teams. [6:55]\n* Resolve pending tickets related to payment and technical issues. [11:31]',5,'2026-04-01 06:21:25','2026-04-01 06:21:25'),(149,'marketing-standup-daily-wed','2026-03-30',':headphones: Huddle notes: 01/04/2026 with @Nandha and @AnirudhSlack AI took notes for this huddle from 11:47:25 - 11:51:44 GMT+5:30. Nandha and Anirudh conducted a performance marketing meeting to review campaign metrics, language-wise spending, and discuss upcoming creative and reporting strategies. View huddle in channel\n\n:handshake: Attendees\n\n@Nandha and @Anirudh\n\n:star: Summary\n\n* Campaign Performance Metrics\n    * @Nandha and @Anirudh reviewed total campaign spending of 8.31, with Google campaigns accounting for 68K in expenditure. [1:50]\n    * Language-wise spending was analyzed, including Tamil Nadu (2.19), Telugu (1.46), Kannada (1.19), and Bengali (5.415) markets. [2:30]\n* Upcoming Campaign Strategy\n    * @Anirudh proposed shifting campaign creatives and reviewing their performance. [3:33]\n    * @Nandha emphasized reviewing creative performance from the last week\'s reporting. [3:45]\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @Anirudh to investigate and resolve user report data access issues. [0:17]\n* @Nandha to review campaign structure and creative performance metrics. [3:59]\n* Both team members to collaborate on analyzing language-specific campaign performance. [3:14]',3,'2026-04-01 06:23:23','2026-04-01 06:23:23'),(150,'ceo-ai-standup-wed','2026-03-30','@J P [0:10]: Mhm Mhm.\n\n@Fida Taneem [0:31]: Good morning, JP\n\n@J P [0:34]: When the Riling\n\n@Fida Taneem [0:42]: Good morning, sir\n\n@J P [0:43]: Take that\n\n@Sneha Pratap [0:44]: Good\n\n@Fida Taneem [0:46]: Hi\n\n@J P [0:48]: What happened today you\'re not well\n\n@Fida Taneem [0:52]: Um Yeah, like the same food, like how I was in my that.\n\n@J P [0:59]: OK, so what happened? So what are the steps here, well, you\'re not well. Then how you fail to work? To work, man, when you are not. See Huh? What man\n\n@J P [1:16]: What they issue the sugar level low are Any other issues\n\n@Fida Taneem [1:20]: Yeah.\n\n@J P [1:22]: Uh.\n\n@Fida Taneem [1:23]: What about it, the sugar, but other complications.\n\n@J P [1:31]: Uh, any other problem,\n\n@Fida Taneem [1:33]: Mm, yeah I overdoses of medicine.\n\n@J P [1:40]: Mhm. So and then what a patent decision. We\'re going to astronomer\n\n@Fida Taneem [1:49]: I mean, it\'s of no use, no, I still have to take that medicine.\n\n@J P [1:56]: OK. Mm So you know, a daily eating food, everything is good.\n\n@Fida Taneem [2:08]: Yeah, that is fine as normal. I\'m doing that.\n\n@J P [2:14]: OK, but you don\'t have that much energy. Right?\n\n@Fida Taneem [2:18]: Mm. How much I eat, there\'s no energy.\n\n@J P [2:23]: Mhm OK More tea. Of the, uh, he sneer.\n\n@Sneha Prata