2026-03-30','* User Registration and Conversion\n    * @Tamil discussed registration processes and tracking user conversion rates across different platforms.\n    * The conversation indicated interest in understanding registered user numbers and conversion percentages.\n* Marketing and Outreach\n    * @Tamil mentioned social media marketing and potential influencer strategies.\n    * Discussion included references to marketing campaigns and tracking their performance.\n* Product Features\n    * Conversation touched on premium user features and potential improvements to the product.\n    * @Bala discussed user trial conversions and potential enhancements to the platform.\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @Tamil to review and potentially improve user registration tracking mechanisms.\n* @Bala to evaluate current marketing campaign performance and influencer strategies.\n* Team to analyze user conversion rates and premium feature adoption.',2,'2026-04-01 06:45:34','2026-04-01 06:45:34'),(153,'cmo-anindita-daily-standup-wed','2026-03-30',':headphones: Huddle notes: 01/04/2026 with @Nandha and @AninditaSlack AI took notes for this huddle from 12:18:25 - 12:47:32 GMT+5:30. Meeting focused on marketing strategy for a new app, discussing regional expansion, social media approach, and content creation across different platforms. View huddle in channel\n\n:handshake: Attendees\n\n@Nandha, @Anindita and @Sneha Sunoj\n\n:star: Summary\n\n* Marketing Campaign Strategy\n    * @Anindita proposed targeting Assam and Maharashtra for initial app marketing, recognizing these regions have less competition and potential for user acquisition: [1:33]\n    * @Anindita recommended starting with a small budget (₹1000-1500 daily) to test market response in Assam: [2:57]\n    * The strategy involves simultaneous campaigns for user and creator registrations: [3:52]\n* Social Media Content Strategy\n    * @Sneha Sunoj emphasized the importance of understanding platform-specific communication, particularly distinguishing between Instagram and LinkedIn approaches: [17:10]\n    * The team agreed to allocate 70% effort to Instagram/Facebook and 30% to LinkedIn: [19:20]\n    * LinkedIn content should focus on professional insights, growth metrics, and company updates: [18:11]\n* Language and Regional Targeting\n    * @Anindita highlighted the potential in Assam, noting increasing interest in content creation and earning opportunities: [27:35]\n    * The team recommended using English as a primary communication language to ensure broad understanding: [12:37]\n    * Content strategy aims to create relatable, region-specific content that can generate viral engagement: [13:35]\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @Nandha to ask social media manager (Bavna) to prepare a one-week content calendar for review: [25:47]\n* @Anindita will provide input on creator onboarding messaging for video content: [9:19]\n* @Sneha Sunoj to coordinate with Bavna on push notification content for review: [28:46]\n* Start marketing campaign in Assam with initial low-budget test: [2:57]\n* Prepare content in Hindi, with potential future expansion to regional languages like Assamese: [4:59]',3,'2026-04-01 07:20:28','2026-04-01 07:20:28'),(154,'cmo-creative-team-daily-standup-wed','2026-03-30',':headphones: Huddle notes: 01/04/2026 with @Nandha and @Krishnan KrishnanSlack AI took notes for this huddle from 13:27:40 - 13:32:00 GMT+5:30. A meeting between @Nandha and @Krishnan Krishnan discussing video production status, focusing on content generation across multiple languages and performance tracking. View huddle in channel\n\n:handshake: Attendees\n\n@Nandha and @Krishnan Krishnan\n\n:star: Summary\n\n* Video Production Status\n    * @Krishnan Krishnan reported generating 10 videos in the last 2 days, primarily in Hindi [1:15].\n    * Today\'s video production will include multiple languages, not just Hindi [1:40].\n    * Plan includes creating 2 videos per person in different languages [1:51].\n* Content Strategy\n    * Discussion about creating videos for audio calls in various languages [1:51].\n    * @Nandha expressed interest in reviewing videos from the last week [1:57].\n    * Exploring performance of UGC and video calls [2:29].\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @Krishnan Krishnan to confirm video completion by today [0:34].\n* @Krishnan Krishnan to collect data from Maniud [3:05].\n* Prepare 3-4 videos across different languages [0:44].\n* Review last week\'s video performance [1:57].',3,'2026-04-01 08:03:26','2026-04-01 08:03:26'),(155,'ceo-ayush-daily-meetup-wed','2026-03-30','Slack AI took notes for this huddle from 17:32:52 - 17:41:17 GMT+5:30. Meeting between @J P and @Ayush Agarwal focused on finalizing preparations for an upcoming Singapore trip, discussing administrative tasks, team updates, and travel logistics. View huddle in channel\n\n:handshake: Attendees\n\n@J P and @Ayush Agarwal\n\n:star: Summary\n\n* Team Updates\n* Singapore Trip Preparation\n* Financial Considerations\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @Ayush Agarwal to complete passport pickup.[1:00]\n* @Ayush Agarwal to purchase two entry passes ($200) for the Singapore trip.[3:45]\n* @J P to search and book a hotel near the event location or airport.[5:33]\n* @Ayush Agarwal to resolve bank payment issues before booking return ticket.[8:03]\n* Confirm international mobile plan details for Singapore trip.[7:57]',4,'2026-04-01 12:13:02','2026-04-01 12:13:02'),(156,'ceo-ai-standup-thu','2026-03-30',':headphones: Huddle notes: 02/04/2026 with @J P and @Sneha PratapSlack AI took notes for this huddle from 10:59:57 - 11:04:24 GMT+5:30. A project status meeting discussing front-end development progress and AI feature implementation with multiple team members. View huddle in channel\n\n:handshake: Attendees\n\n@J P, @Sneha Pratap and @Fida Taneem\n\n:star: Summary\n\n* Front-end Development Status\n    * @Fida Taneem is currently working on the front-end portion of the project, specifically focusing on login functionality [1:11].\n    * @Fida Taneem acknowledged that the current build is not completely meeting project requirements and has identified some missing elements [1:37].\n    * @J P suggested a methodical approach of checking components one by one and referencing existing code for improvements [2:06].\n* AI Feature Refinement\n    * @Sneha Pratap is working on enhancing AI communication characteristics, including:\n        - Introducing more natural typos\n        - Adding emojis contextually\n        - Adjusting message delay timing from 2 to 6-8 seconds [3:12]\n    * The modifications aim to make AI interactions more human-like and situationally appropriate [3:43].\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @Fida Taneem to complete front-end development by tomorrow evening and present progress in the morning meeting [2:31].\n* @Sneha Pratap to continue testing AI feature implementations with new communication parameters [3:43].',1,'2026-04-02 05:35:34','2026-04-02 05:35:34'),(157,'ops-standup-daily-thu','2026-03-30','Summary\n\n* Individual Performance Metrics\n    * @Ranjini completed 30 calls, focusing on PAN card verification and follow-ups with users. [2:04]\n    * @Deeksha made 25 calls and received positive responses from some users about completing required tasks. [2:47]\n    * @Reshma Reshma made 2 calls, informing users about documentation and verification deadlines. [3:01]\n    * @Gousia completed 25 calls and confirmed ongoing communication with users. [3:31]\n* PAN Card Verification Strategy\n    * Team members are following up with users about PAN card verification, with a clear deadline of April 6th. [2:26]\n    * Users are being informed about the importance of completing verification before the deadline. [2:21]\n* Revenue and User Engagement Challenge\n    * Significant revenue drop observed between 7-10 PM, potentially due to IPL (Indian Premier League). [6:19]\n    * @Sneha Sunoj requested team to develop creative ideas for attracting users during this period. [4:40]\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @Ranjini to complete remaining calls by tomorrow evening. [3:52]\n* All team members to develop innovative notifications for FIFO user and creator sides. [4:58]\n* @Sneha Sunoj plans to modify AI prompts to improve accuracy. [5:02]\n* Team to brainstorm and share ideas for increasing user engagement during IPL. [6:41]',5,'2026-04-02 06:09:27','2026-04-02 06:09:27'),(158,'product_manager-daily-standup-tamil-thu','2026-03-30','* Performance Metrics\n    * @Bala mentioned metrics related to registration and subscriber numbers, with references to figures like 210, 22, and 498. [9:25]\n    * Discussion suggests tracking monthly performance and returns, though specifics are unclear. [7:04]\n\n\n* Development and Marketing\n    * Conversation touched on development work and marketing content preparation. [11:38]\n    * @Tamil indicated ongoing efforts to develop and prepare marketing materials. [11:21]',2,'2026-04-02 06:31:19','2026-04-02 06:31:19'),(159,'product_manager-daily-standup-dhanush-thu','2026-03-30','* Professional Networking\n    * @Dhanush discussed leveraging LinkedIn for marketing and networking purposes, emphasizing the importance of professional connections. [1:39]\n    * @Dhanush mentioned exploring premium account options for enhanced networking capabilities. [1:58]\n* Meeting Scheduling\n    * @Bala confirmed a meeting scheduled for 12:30, with potential follow-up discussions around 2:00 PM and 3:00 PM. [3:48][3:54]\n    * Both participants seemed to be coordinating multiple meeting times and discussing availability. [3:39]\n* Project Progress\n    * @Dhanush reported on various progress metrics, including registrations (121), video reports (183), and business ideas (95). [5:17][5:50][6:00]\n    * Discussion included app design, flow monitoring, and content development progress. [6:10][6:47]\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @Dhanush to review and potentially upgrade LinkedIn networking strategy. [1:39]\n* @Bala to prepare for meetings scheduled at 12:30, 2:00 PM, and 3:00 PM. [3:48][3:54]\n* Both participants to continue monitoring app design and development progress. [6:10]\n* @Dhanush to provide detailed report on content completion and progress tracking. [6:26]',2,'2026-04-02 06:41:16','2026-04-02 06:41:16'),(160,'cmo-anindita-daily-standup-thu','2026-03-30',':headphones: Huddle notes: 02/04/2026 with @Nandha and @AninditaSlack AI took notes for this huddle from 12:07:59 - 12:30:24 GMT+5:30. A strategic discussion between a Growth Manager and Performance Marketer about improving user acquisition and creator engagement across different regions of India, with a focus on addressing conversion challenges. View huddle in channel\n\n:handshake: Attendees\n\n@Nandha and @Anindita\n\n:star: Summary\n\n* Regional Marketing Strategy\n    * @Anindita highlighted that current marketing efforts are primarily focused on Hindi-speaking mainland Indian states, with less attention to regions like Assam and West Bengal.[3:02]\n    * The team recognizes significant potential in tier 3 and tier 4 cities, particularly in Assam, where social media usage is growing among content creators.[4:59]\n    * External factors like elections and IPL can significantly impact user engagement and registration rates across different regions.[18:53]\n* Creator Onboarding Experience\n    * A specific user experience issue was identified where new creators are confused about how to handle incoming calls on the platform.[10:16]\n    * @Anindita proposed creating a comprehensive Hindi-language explainer video to guide creators through the platform\'s interaction process.[12:36]\n    * The proposed video would be mandatory for new creators and potentially translated into regional languages.[14:26]\n* Platform Visual Design\n    * Current creator avatars were criticized as being too childish and generic, potentially reducing user engagement.[22:02]\n    * @Anindita suggested creating more regionally specific and attractive avatars that would appeal to users in different linguistic regions.[24:20]\n    * The goal is to design avatars that look genuine and \"sexy\" to tempt users into engaging with the platform.[22:43]\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @Anindita will contact Bala to discuss creating a Hindi explainer video for creators and get detailed input on the platform\'s interaction process.[13:22]\n* @Anindita will collaborate with the design team to develop more regionally specific and appealing creator avatars.[23:05]\n* Develop a marketing strategy specifically tailored for Assam, considering the unique social media landscape and ongoing elections.[19:19]\n* Investigate and address the low conversion rates in the Bengali region by understanding underlying technical or user experience issues.[9:24]\n\nThis tool uses AI to generate notes, so some information may be inaccurate. They\'re based on the huddle transcript and thread and can be edited anytime.',3,'2026-04-02 07:12:43','2026-04-02 07:12:43'),(161,'ceo-ayush-daily-meetup-thu','2026-03-30',':headphones: Huddle notes: 02/04/2026 with @Ayush Agarwal and @J PSlack AI took notes for this huddle from 12:35:18 - 12:40:14 GMT+5:30. Meeting between @J P and @Ayush Agarwal focused on financial transactions, bank account management, and ongoing administrative tasks related to their organization. View huddle in channel\n\n:handshake: Attendees\n\n@J P and @Ayush Agarwal\n\n:star: Summary\n\n* Bank Account Management\n    * @Ayush Agarwal is in the process of unfreezing an account with SGFC and experiencing issues with ES Bank\'s debit card on UPI.[0:30]\n    * @Ayush Agarwal is changing the bank account to US Bank and will keep Yes Bank for major payments and settlements.[1:20]\n    * They plan to transfer funds periodically to the new account to manage financial operations.[3:13]\n* Financial Documentation\n    * @Ayush Agarwal is preparing to calculate total revenue for the financial year and March expenses.[1:25]\n    * Google TDS documents need to be physically printed and signed.[0:54]\n    * Phone pay contact has already been signed and shared.[0:54]\n* Team Internship Updates\n    * A finance intern is currently working on a PowerPoint presentation for tax saving purposes.[4:39]\n    * A new intern named Irisha has joined the founder\'s office, though her active engagement is yet to be determined.[4:07]\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @Ayush Agarwal to complete financial year revenue calculation and finalize March expense format.[1:25]\n* @Ayush Agarwal to print and sign Google TDS documents.[0:54]\n* @Ayush Agarwal to check and submit tax-related PPT to CA.[4:39]\n* @Ayush Agarwal to pick up passport.[4:53]',1,'2026-04-02 07:13:12','2026-04-02 07:13:12'),(162,'cmo-creative-team-daily-standup-thu','2026-03-30',':headphones: Huddle notes: 02/04/2026 with @Nandha and @Krishnan KrishnanSlack AI took notes for this huddle from 12:30:54 - 12:45:01 GMT+5:30. A team meeting discussing video production status, upcoming team expansion, content creation workflow, and individual task assignments across marketing and design functions. View huddle in channel\n\n:handshake: Attendees\n\n@Nandha, @Krishnan Krishnan, @anas and @Sooraj\n\n:star: Summary\n\n* Video Production Status\n    * @Krishnan Krishnan reported completing 3 videos personally and having 1 additional video from Disha, totaling 4 videos. [1:01]\n    * Team was instructed to stop working at night due to potential issues. [1:27]\n    * Productivity might temporarily decrease due to onboarding new team members. [2:45]\n* Team Expansion and Training\n    * New team members are joining, requiring comprehensive training this week. [2:37]\n    * Training will focus on teaching new joiners how to use specific tools and workflows. [2:45]\n    * Expected temporary reduction in production rates during training period. [2:45]\n* Content Creation and Posting\n    * @Krishnan Krishnan is working on developing consistent design templates for video and poster content. [10:39]\n    * Team discussing strategies for social media content creation and posting. [8:31]\n    * Emphasis on maintaining visual consistency across different content types. [10:07]\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @Krishnan Krishnan to complete training for new team members this week. [2:37]\n* @Krishnan Krishnan to produce 2 additional videos and coordinate 3 more from the team. [3:18]\n* Team to develop and standardize content templates for consistent branding. [10:07]\n* @anas to edit pending videos and coordinate with team. [12:57]',3,'2026-04-02 08:39:41','2026-04-02 08:39:41'),(163,'full-stack-dev-astro-standup-thu','2026-03-30','Summary\n\n* Sprint and Work Status\n    * @Barkha Agarwal indicated they have not been working for 3 days [1:00].\n    * @Rishabh Kumar inquired about the current sprint progress [1:02].\n* UI and Design Concerns\n    * @Rishabh Kumar noted inconsistent color schemes across the dashboard and profile page [2:43].\n    * The current UI was deemed \"not good enough\" by both participants [2:07], [2:12].\n    * @Rishabh Kumar observed that the logo appears visually underwhelming [3:32].\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @Barkha Agarwal to update the profile page and standardize color schemes [2:16].\n* @Rishabh Kumar plans to connect with another team member to discuss UI changes [3:03].\n* Implement consistent color usage across dashboard and profile page interfaces.',35,'2026-04-02 20:35:13','2026-04-02 20:35:13'),(164,'full-stack-dev-astro-standup-fri','2026-03-30','Summary\n\n* Development Status\n    * @Barkha Agarwal has updated UI colors and is working on dashboard and logo panel modifications [2:12].\n    * Currently, payment integration is functioning locally but not yet server-integrated [1:26].\n    * Approximately 5-6 tasks remain incomplete in the current sprint [5:32].\n* Payment Integration\n    * Razor payment integration is pending and cannot be completed immediately [1:39].\n    * @Barkha Agarwal is currently working on local implementation of payment features [1:09].\n* Website Launch Plan\n    * @Rishabh Kumar plans to review the website once all current tasks are completed [6:07].\n    * After internal review, the website will be made publicly accessible [6:07].\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @Barkha Agarwal to complete remaining 5-6 UI/UX tasks today [5:42].\n* @Barkha Agarwal to update upgrade buttons, cards, and input elements [5:08].\n* @Rishabh Kumar to review website after @Barkha Agarwal completes current development tasks [5:45].\n* Defer Razor payment system full integration until further technical readiness [1:39].',35,'2026-04-03 06:04:05','2026-04-03 06:04:05'),(165,'marketing-standup-daily-fri','2026-03-30',':headphones: Huddle notes: 03/04/2026 with @Nandha and @AnirudhSlack AI took notes for this huddle from 11:36:44 - 11:46:29 GMT+5:30. Performance marketing meeting between @Anirudh and @Nandha focused on analyzing campaign performance across multiple Indian languages and states, reviewing recent metrics and optimization strategies. View huddle in channel\n\n:handshake: Attendees\n\n@Nandha and @Anirudh\n\n:star: Summary\n\n* Campaign Performance Metrics\n    * @Anirudh reported total spend of 91 yesterday, with significant improvements in key performance indicators [8:48].\n    * Conversions increased from 350 to 412, and purchase value rose from 39,000 to 45,000 [8:56].\n    * Registrations saw a substantial jump from 360 to 637 across different language markets [8:56].\n* Language and State Targeting\n    * Discussed performance across multiple Indian languages, including Telugu, Tamil, Malayalam, Kannada, and Bengali [5:44].\n    * @Nandha suggested focusing on state-specific targeting to optimize campaign performance [2:06].\n    * Noted that Hindi and other regional markets show varying performance levels [1:04].\n* Campaign Optimization Strategies\n    * @Anirudh mentioned potentially moving to new CBO (Campaign Budget Optimization) campaigns that are outperforming current setups [0:36].\n    * Discussed potential challenges with narrow targeting, which might increase cost per acquisition (CPA) [2:14].\n    * Considered reusing creative assets across different language and state campaigns [2:33].\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @Anirudh to investigate reporting center bug preventing full conversion data visibility [2:56].\n* @Nandha to continue analyzing performance across different language markets and refine targeting strategies [2:06].\n* Review and potentially scale successful campaign creatives across different language regions [3:46].',3,'2026-04-03 06:19:36','2026-04-03 06:19:36'),(166,'ops-standup-daily-fri','2026-03-30','Summary\n\n* Daily Task Reporting\n    * @Nisha a completed 14 tickets and 58 onboarding verifications yesterday [5:29].\n    * Team members reported varying task completions: @Ranjini did 20 tickets and 15 onboarding tasks, @Deeksha completed 25 calls, @Reshma Reshma handled 17 onboarding and 7 tickets [7:23].\n    * A significant backlog of 57 pending onboarding verifications was identified that requires immediate attention [5:59].\n* Notification Verification\n    * @Sneha Sunoj requested team to track notification delivery for users and creators [1:17].\n    * Specific focus on IPL notifications for upcoming weekend, with @Reshma Reshma assigned to handle creator notifications and @Gousia assigned to manage user notifications [14:09].\n    * Team instructed to verify notification types and ensure proper delivery [2:39].\n* Team Transition\n    * @Ranjini is preparing to transition out of the current role, with a planned handover to @Anjali bhatt [19:53].\n    * New team members @Anjali bhatt (Anjali) and @Nisha a (Nisha) are being integrated and trained on onboarding processes [21:01].\n    * @Sneha Sunoj will oversee the transition and provide guidance during the handover period [27:53].\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @Nisha a must complete 57 pending onboarding verifications by end of day [5:59].\n* @Reshma Reshma to track and create 5 creator-side IPL notifications for Saturday and Sunday [14:09].\n* @Gousia to track and create 5 user-side IPL notifications for Saturday and Sunday [14:09].\n* @Anjali bhatt to log in and out daily, messaging @Sneha Sunoj about work status [24:29].\n* @Ranjini to assist in comprehensive handover process for @Anjali bhatt, focusing on onboarding and ticket resolution procedures [21:01].',5,'2026-04-03 06:45:03','2026-04-03 06:45:03'),(167,'cmo-creative-team-daily-standup-fri','2026-03-30',':headphones: Huddle notes: 03/04/2026 with @Nandha and @SoorajSlack AI took notes for this huddle from 13:07:26 - 13:21:39 GMT+5:30. The meeting focused on developing a social connection app for Bangalore, discussing marketing strategies, content creation, and design elements for promoting the platform. View huddle in channel\n\n:handshake: Attendees\n\n@Sooraj, @Nandha and @Krishnan Krishnan\n\n:star: Summary\n\n* App Concept and Branding\n    * @Sooraj developed poster designs with key messaging like \"Connect Bangalore People Instantly\" and \"Meet New People and Make New Friends\"[1].\n    * The app aims to facilitate instant connections, calls, chats, and meetups for Bangalore residents[1].\n    * @Nandha discussed targeting both local and educated populations in Bangalore[4:21].\n* Marketing Content Strategy\n    * @Krishnan Krishnan mentioned preparing 6 videos and planning content across different categories like audio calls, video calls, and user-generated content[7:56].\n    * The team plans to create unique creatives for different audience segments, with a focus on language and targeting specifics[9:21].\n    * Influencer videos are being considered as part of the marketing approach[12:32].\n* Performance and Targeting\n    * @Krishnan Krishnan reported that out of 25 content pieces, 13 are performing well[9:15].\n    * The team is planning to segment content by numbers, language, and creative variations[9:21].\n    * Targeting is being refined, with a focus on specific age groups and demographics[11:54].\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @Sooraj to finalize app poster designs with playstore icon and app logo[1].\n* @Krishnan Krishnan to prepare a Google sheet tracking content performance by category and language[8:17].\n* @Nandha to review and approve marketing content across different creative categories[12:04].\n* Team to develop unique UGC and influencer content for the Bangalore market[12:32].',3,'2026-04-03 07:52:08','2026-04-03 07:58:10'),(168,'cmo-anindita-daily-standup-fri','2026-03-30',':headphones: Huddle notes: 03/04/2026 with @Nandha and @AninditaSlack AI took notes for this huddle from 12:08:31 - 12:26:34 GMT+5:30. Meeting between @Anindita and @Nandha focused on discussing current product challenges, new campaigns, potential feature improvements for Haima, and strategies for market expansion in Hindi-speaking regions. View huddle in channel\n\n:handshake: Attendees\n\n@Nandha and @Anindita\n\n:star: Summary\n\n* Analytics Portal Technical Issues\n    * @Anindita reported that the analytics portal is not functioning correctly, with missing conversion data and language-specific problems [0:17].\n    * The dashboard is not displaying data for Bengali and Hindi languages, and loading times are slow [1:12].\n    * @Nandha acknowledged the issues and mentioned that an analytics team member will be working on resolving them [1:33].\n* New Campaigns and Market Performance\n    * Two new campaigns went live yesterday afternoon, with reports updated in a new sheet [2:07].\n    * Current user acquisition is consistent at around 45,000-50,000 users [16:11].\n    * Regions like Maharashtra, Gujarat, Uttar Pradesh are performing well in terms of conversions [3:11].\n* Product Feature Discussions\n    * @Anindita and Bala discussed potential features to enhance user-creator interactions, including conversation starters and game-like interaction prompts [8:34].\n    * Proposed adding a \"Hi\" button next to creator profiles to facilitate initial contact [11:35].\n    * Discussed auto-payment implementation similar to free trial models like Canva, with a notification-based approach [13:14].\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @Anindita will connect with Airud to understand campaign performance and creator availability in different regions [15:17].\n* @Anindita will talk to Sneha about increasing Hindi creator registrations [15:17].\n* @Anindita will prepare and share the explainer video script with @Nandha for review before sending to Krishna [17:08].\n* @Anindita needs to clarify the specifics of peak-hour earnings for creators with Nega [17:36].\n* @Nandha will review the explainer video script and provide feedback [17:13].\n\nThis tool uses AI to generate notes, so some information may be inaccurate. They\'re based on the',3,'2026-04-03 07:52:16','2026-04-03 07:52:16'),(169,'product_manager-daily-standup-dhanush-fri','2026-03-30','* Platform User Experience\n    * @Bala emphasized creating a user-friendly home screen with clear host registration and onboarding processes. [3:21]\n    * The platform will support different user types, including professionals, students, and local community members aged 18 and above. [41:05]\n    * Navigation and user interface design were discussed to ensure intuitive and engaging user interactions. [23:57]\n* User Demographics and Targeting\n    * @Nandha highlighted a user base skewing towards females (approximately 95%), with a focus on professionals and college students. [41:58]\n    * The platform aims to create localized, age-specific content targeting users between 40-45 years old. [41:37]\n    * Diverse user engagement strategies were proposed to attract different professional and educational backgrounds. [40:02]\n* Technical Development\n    * @Dhanush stressed the importance of smooth user flows, minimal loading times, and responsive design across different devices. [51:46]\n    * Current platform metrics include 168 registrations, 440 trials, and 1 premium user, with 333 video watch counts. [45:32]\n    * Future development will focus on improving payment gateways, chat functionality, and overall user experience. [52:35]\n* Business Strategy\n    * @Bala proposed a marketing strategy with 60% focus on brand awareness and 40% on host retention and operations. [33:54]\n    * The platform will implement weekly payouts for hosts and create incentives for high-performing users. [35:55]\n    * Branding will emphasize local connections and professional networking opportunities. [31:48]\n\n:white_check_mark: Action items\n\n* @Bala to finalize home screen design with clear host registration process. [12:25]\n* @Dhanush to complete technical testing and ensure smooth user flows before launch. [48:40]\n* @Nandha to develop targeted marketing materials focusing on professional and student demographics. [44:12]\n* Team to review and optimize payment mechanisms and chat functionality. [52:35]\n* Conduct further user research to validate demographic targeting strategies. [42:52]',2,'2026-04-03 13:13:57','2026-04-03 13:13:57');
